\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, quite a lot of difference to the family. That meant that mother had to work. Go out to work, she went out to work all day long which she got a half a crown - for doing the house - work in another 
- somebody else's house, and - I used to go out doorstep cleaning. Tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was while you were still at school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Tuppence for the step and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 pence for the brass I charged. Then mother took in washing, and she took in other peoples mangling which was three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 ha'pence a dozen, which we had to do, children. And - also we let - one of the rooms for a doctor. Because there wasn't many doctors about. So - we let him - have a - one room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He was quite an exclusive lodger wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. Which was a plate outside, a brass plate, you know, like there usually are in doctor's places which we had to clean, and put the chairs out in the hall before ever we went to school and see the s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 tep was cleaned, that was heart }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 stoned in those days, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The chairs were for a waiting room were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, outside in the hall. Yes. Then when we came back from school we had to take the medicine out. Deliver it. Which was wrapped up in white paper those days, sealed - with red - sealing wax. Got a penny a week for that I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He wasn't over-generous then was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born, if you can give her time of death and her age at death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 My mother died - three years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That's 1968?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And she was ninety-four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Grays, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did she work before marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, she worked before she was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know what sort of work it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In service. Yes. Housekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She'd work at odd times when your father was unemployed after marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, she worked very very hard indeed my mother did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of hours would she work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 All day long, right - and she never used to go to bed 'til about eleven, used to be up at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning. Yes. I can't understand why she lived so long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was sign}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
writing a bit of a chancy occupation in those days then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. It was. Used to be Gold leaf you know, sign}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 writing and - but of course it used to be so cheap - ly done, to - money didn't come in very freely. So whatever we done as children - brothers as well - they had to give the money to mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who looked after the children while your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We looked after
 ourselves. Yes. And - the eldest one cooked the dinner. Sometimes it was me. Which I used to love cooking. Yes, loved it, yes. Always have done, right up 'til today. Yes. Yes, well I'm very fond of - anything I can do, what me hands can do. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many rooms were there in the house you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Three bedrooms, two sitting rooms, a kitchen, scullery. Nice back garden, and front garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You had this one lodger who was a doctor? Was he self-contained or did he eat with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh n
o, no, no. No. He just had it mornings and evenings, then went home - which is proper surgery was at the top of Muswell Hill. Well down at the foot of the hill was no - doctors whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He used one of your sitting rooms did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 As - yes. As - for his surgery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So he had a surgery there, he didn't actually live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, never lived there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. No, my 
mother wash - done all the washing and done other peoples washing as well. We had to go up to Muswell Hill and collect - quite six to eight peoples washing, round Muswell Hill Broadway, and mother used to do it quick 'cos she wanted the money, and used to
 be about half a crown she got for that - dozens of things which she washed for the one person alone. And ironed them. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Washing was no easy job in those days was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, well we had a boiler, which we lit a fire underneath it, a copper. Yes. A
nd of course we had a nice back garden where you could dry them. Perhaps there used to be three peoples washings done by the time I came home from school which I had to take home, all wrapped up nicely in - and come back and give the money to your mother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about your clothes, were they new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well, I had a - an aunt, which she had - two or three girls, my age. And their clothes were sent on to my mother. They was more or less second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 hand clothes. But - but - good - clothes. They weren't rags, they was very very good clothes. And I used to be very proud when I used to have them on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother ever buy clothes from the second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 hand shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They'd just come from the family or people you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Or
 - at school you see you could - take a piece of material and make some clothes, which I used to, I was very fond of it. Mother said it's - you can't have any more today, you've already had some last week, but - I was always asking for some material. Whic
h we could make things at school. Which was very handy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother make any clothes or mend clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, oh yes, yes. My mother never bought any baby's clothes what came along. Never. My mother made the - all of them. Every one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about shoes, were they new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
New. New. Yes. We had to save up our money in boxes. Perhaps if somebody give us an extra penny or anything like that we had it in - our own moneybox. Then - you could buy - a pair of shoes for five shillings, a very very nice pair for five shil}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 lings. And really look really a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 off. - Especially on the Sunday when you went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any special time for buying clothes or just when you needed them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, only when we needed them, never any special time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your father help your mother with any jobs in the houses, would he do any cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never. Never. My father never helped at all in the house. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would he do anything like getting the coal in or the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, nothing at all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he consider this part of his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well he - I've never seen my father - help anything like that, never. More or less, if I speak the truth, my f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 ather was on the lazy six}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would he help with the young children, would he undress or bath any of the babies
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Definitely not. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
You told me that you had odd jobs to do to earn the odd money and help your mother by running errands and things. Did you have any other regular tasks in the home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, we had all - scrub the hall, the kitchen, and we had a - a fender which we used to - hearth - hearthstone it, black}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 lead, clean the - soot out, 'cos we used to cook by an oven, a coal fire with an oven to it it was. And with a hot water 
by the side which was a brass tap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have gas there at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never any gas no. No gas at all, my mother cooked - all by this - range, cooking range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have gas for lighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, we had gas for lighting, on the wall w
ith a - mantles, they used to go by mantle, for the - gas. Was - only gas - downstairs and one - gas in mother's room, not in our rooms, not in the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s room, we had a candle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 These household tasks, did each child have a particular job of their own to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No everybody had a job to do. Everybody had a job to do. See every handle of the door was brass. All that had to be cleaned, it was your turn one week, and your other sister's another week. Knives, forks and spoons was - had to be done on 
the Saturday. IT WAS YOUR TURN ONE WEEK. Brother's or sister's the next week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Brothers had to do housework as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Brother had to help as well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long did you continue helping in the home like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Until I left school - at thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Then the younger ones would take over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They would carry on. And I - went into service then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult, did you help them dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - rather, oh yes, I was pa
ssionately fond of my brothers, I wouldn't let 'em be touched or anything, no, I dressed them, take them out - and - and used to go round to different houses and perhaps see if they've got a - younger baby so I could have that in me arms. That - I was ver
y fond of that. Especially on the Sunday. Every Sunday I used to do that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 Knock at the houses, and see if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
 anybody had had a new baby, so I could bring it home - and show my - mother and father. Then me father used to take photographs of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you didn't seem to find these jobs a chore at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Not at all. No, I used to love - I used to love children. Yes. I would never it my father touch any - body. I'd stand in front so he just gave me the clout. Instead of them having it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, they'd do anything I'd ask, if I wanted anything, they'd - go and get it for me or anything like that. If mother was ill so anything - especially if mother was ill they'd - help you then, you know, they wer
e very - upset if mother was - in bed, which was very very seldom. I can only remember once - when me mother was in bed. And that really upset all - all of us. Because we knew we'd got to turn to, and do the lot. All the housework, and - run and get the e
rrands and cook the dinner and see the other children went to bed, everything was washed, cleaned before ever mother come downstairs again. Nothing left - dirty when mother came - got up again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That was quite an achievement.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, we was - wasn't allowed to go out to play - like other children do in the streets, nothing like that at all, wasn't allowed that, no. Never allowed to go out in the street to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did you used to play then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the garden. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
My father wouldn't allow it. Because for one thing there wasn't a field or anything to play on. It meant that we had to play in the street. And my father wo
uldn't do that, or let us do that if - any time he saw us playing in the - street we had a - jolly good hiding. Because you see - having a doctor's surgery there we never knew when he would - go and that was - just show my father up and he wouldn't allow 
that. Wasn't going to have that. We - and we couldn't have children in, unless we asked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You could get permission to have other children in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If we asked could we have a friend in and play with us, yes, but if we - had them in without asking we'd 
get a jolly good hiding for that. And it wasn't just an ordinary good hiding, it used to be with a stick. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He was quite severe was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Very severe. You weren't allowed to sit at the table - unless you got up to the table and said your grace,
 for what you're going to receive. And if you said for what you had received, when you hadn't had anything, you'd get down. Had nothing. Because your mind wasn't on what you were going to do. That's what he was like. And that's what he was like, my father
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He'd really stick to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 My father was very very strict indeed. Well, to me - I thought he was very cruel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That sounds very harsh indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mm. Well he was to me once, when I forgot to put the - tea - where you stand your teapot on. 
I forgot to put that, and he just bashed me head up against the wall for - forgetting to do that, 'cos me mind wasn't on, I was - thinking about - getting out to play he said. Just for a little thing like that. Well - I never. I used to try to remember be
cause I knew what I'd get if I never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh - no, nobody put us to bed at all, you see to yourself, you wash yourself - you had to show yourself to see that you had washed yourself before you went to bed. And usually - bed at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What were the sleeping arrangements in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - used to be three in a bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have double beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, three in a bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You had three bedrooms did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Three bedrooms, but they're very very small. Weren't large bedrooms, you couldn't run round in them. They were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So your mother and father would be in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mother and father and the cot usually be in that room you see. Dressing table and that. Then there 
used to be the boys room and the girls room. Yes, three in a bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh we had a bathroom. A - a very small bathroom. Yes, a very small bathroom we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That was quite advanced for the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And that was always - once a week you had your bath. Once a week you had your - brimstone and treacle. And - li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 orice powder the next week, whether you liked it or not you had it. Mm, you lined up for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Is that when you had your change of clothes, bath night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bath{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 night. Once a week. Had to put the copper on for that though. And you had to take your water up in buckets. No - hot - water laid on, not in those days. Nothing like that. Every bit of water was carried upstairs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But it had an actual bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Had - had a bath, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did the family have their meals, which room did you use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Down in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any occasions when you ate in one of the other rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Your mother had the coal oven. At what time would you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What members of the family would be there for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well you're all supposed to be there at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} for - your breakfast. Unless - you were - sent up to Muswell Hill - queuing up for bread, then
 you had to get up at seven and run quickly up to Muswell Hill to be the first in the queue. Get three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
pennorth of stale bread. Then you - hurry up home, if you couldn't get it at once shop you run round to another bakers, see you - perhaps knock somebody over this - if that's going to get in your way so that you get in the queue before them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You really had to get this bread did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We really had to get this bread, yes. It was really terrible if you went home with no bread, which was very very s
eldom. If Wiley's had sold out, which was the shop there now still, Muswell Hill, and used to be one - just round the corner. I used to tear like anything to get round to there. To get this bread. Of course perhaps there used to be a little piece of - mak
eweight in there and I could eat that walking down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Coney Hatch Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} home again you see. Nobody knew about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would your father be there for breakfast or would he have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, me father be there for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
For breakfast, we had - three slices - only - either of margarine - dripping, or marmalade. No more than that whether you liked it or not, and a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You couldn't ask for a second helping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never ask f
or a second helping, never. And - it used - marmalade those days used to be in two pound jars, which you never see these days. And when the jar was empty, perhaps it was your turn, you - knelt up on your chair with your three slices of dry bread, and wipe
d round the jar. And that was your breakfast, then somebody'd open the door for you so you'd go out and - wash your hands. You all took it in turns to have this - marmalade jar. And that was your - yes, and that was your - breakfast. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Then how did you get on for your {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Midday{\*\xmlclose} meal, we always - had a nice - dinner, hot meal that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you used to come home from school for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - everybody come home from school for their meal, those who were - were near. Just two of 
them went to - right to over Friern Barnet way, which I wasn't strong enough those - days to go over that way. Then they had their dinner when they came home. But - perhaps I or my other brother had got to go up to the butchers to get the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  six}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
pennorth of
 beef pieces and a pennorth of beef suet, or - six - pennorth of scrag, or - pigs fry, which you never hear of today. And pigs fry used to make a lovely - dish. Because they used to have - onions - layer of pigs fry and a layer of potatoes, and so on, lik
e that. We had a very large - dish, and that used to go in the oven. Then perhaps one of me other sister's had gone up the farm to get some skimmed milk. And mother used to make a nice - bread pudding, or - rice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You still had farms at Muswell Hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not now, no, not now. No farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But you did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was still fairly open was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, it was - it was very open - when I was young. Yes. Yes, I used to love to go to the farm. 'Cos used to get - take a bazin and get two}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
pennorth of cracked eggs as well. You'd get a - basinful for tuppence. Cracked eggs. One thing about my mother, she would make a - some rock cakes on a Sunday, that's the only - time you had homemade cakes. And one of you'd like out the dish with 
your finger, you know, the basin. I used to - wait 'til it was my turn, see that I had it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you have any pudding or sweet after the main course?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Every day we had a sweet. Yes. Yes. Either bread pudding or a - rice pudding or - spotted 
dick. A plain pudding with treacle. We had a little tiny shop opposite - our house, which you could take a basin and get two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
pennyworth of jam or two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 pennyworth of treacle, anything like that, and two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 pennorth of pickles. Get a nice lot too. For that money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would you do for your evening meal, what did you you're your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh we only had - just bread and butter. Or marma - sometimes mother would make a little jam. But - you still had your three slices. But perhaps once a week - one of you had to go up to Wiley's again - and get - see if you can get two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
penny worth of stale cakes, which we often did get, very very seldom we went home without any stale cakes, then there'd be one each for you, just once a week. And always this rock cake on a Sunday, homemade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would your father and mother have the same food as you or would they have something extra to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never any - no, no, no, never had anything different to what we did. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about Sundays, would your meals be any different on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, there used to be a aitch bones as a rule on a Sunday, with a - a large Yorkshire pudding and - greens, always had - my mother always believe in greens and plenty of potatoes. And a pudding always. Perhaps a steamed pudding 
with jam at the bottom, which we used to like, or - roly-poly with sultanas and that in, with custard. Or - perhaps we used to have - custard and figs, 'cos - those days }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 
you see you could get them chea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 p, very very cheap those days. Get a pound of figs for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 pence a pound. Or - pound of prunes perhaps for sixpence a pound, nice - very large ones.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would Sunday tea be anything special or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, it - the only thing we had - was - this rock cake. That was our special tea. And you could have a 
little jam on your - mar - margarine, on a Sunday. That was the only difference you had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say your mother used to make her own jam sometimes, did she do anything else like that, did she ever bottle any fruit or vegetables?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no, we never had
 time for anything like that, no, unless it was - never anything put by, what we - what - jam she made - you know, just lasted the week. Anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about pickles or bread or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh we never made anything like that, no. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about home made wines or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Nothing like that whatever, that was never in the family. No. The only drink we had - and that was if we was very very good - at Christmas time we either - we had a hot blackcurrant drink, or a 
hot peppermint drink which you bought in a pint bottle, at the shop. That's if you were very very good, you had that Christmas time, that was a luxury. Father and mother had the same. Yes, never - never any - alcohol in our house whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Your parents were teetotallers were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Absolutely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they grow any of their own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 A few cabbages and - 'cos we never had so - you know - 'cos there was always lines of washing out. Used to have some - cabbages and - ma
rrows, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Nothing like that at all. No, never any - saw any tinned - fruit or anything like that, the only tin - I used to see - that was really for the - it was a tin of Nestles m
ilk, which when mother went out you see, if she - the tine was open I could just dip me finger in - and have a little - which I loved. But it wasn't me what done it though of course not. Somebody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they used to buy fresh vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh, fresh vegetables, that used to come round on a barrow. See in those days you see - well it was - pea time - they used to call that peck. Three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 pence a peck of peas. Same as gooseberries or anything like that, it was always in peck. Chopped wood. 
A basketful of chopped wood, tuppence. Logs - get no end of - logs for sixpence. Throw them in the back yard. They hadn't got room in the cellar for all that lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you keep any livestock, any hens or rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, only rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were they kept for food or just pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well we ate them when - yes. When they were ready - we ate them but we were a little bit upset when we - had to eat them, but still - we ate them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Every day. YES? EVERY day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember eating tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never had any tinned meat, no, never had that. And of course my mother used to believe in making brawn. It's a - thing she did make, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 braw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 n. Used to have - pigs head, and then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 pennorth of leg of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You were telling me about the brawn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. My mother used to have that on the kitchen range. And - then we used to watch her. She used to mash it all up, and put it through a sieve. Then she used to put it in basins, and the next da
y you see that all used to be set, and that was cut that thick, and that used - we used to have that, perhaps for the dinner the next day. That was in the summer more or less we had that. And that was really beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever get any rabbits from poachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, no, no, no, never nothing like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You think she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She went without a lot, my mother did. We used to have to g
o sometimes see if we could get a hock of bacon you know - then - that would make a difference, you could perhaps get a nice hock of bacon, and - she'd boil that so she could put some dum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 
plings in it and make some peas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  pudding. You never hear or that today, people doing hock of bacon. Few onions in it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 
, dumplings, and make some peas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  pudding, beautiful. Some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would your father have more than your mother or the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 My father used to see that he had his share, oh yes. Yes. Definitely. Mother was the one what went without, but not father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never. Oh no, never. Never allowed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, you - what was put on your plate you had to eat, and if you never ate it at dinnertime you had it for your tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And that'd really come up would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That would really come up, if you couldn't eat that at dinnertime, you had it for your tea broug
ht up. You never had anything 'til you cleared your plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about if you wanted something like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it or help yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The salt? It only used to be salt and pepper on the table. Nothing any - anything else
. That was put on - whatever was put on was put out the saucepan onto your plate. Whether you liked it or whether you not, you - it was put in front of you to eat. And if you couldn't eat it, well you had it brought up for the next meal. But if they reall
y found out - that you were - sick after it then that - be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you more or less had to prove that something didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Had - had - you had to prove that you couldn't - take it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never had a second helping, no. No. No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you bring a toy or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - gracious, never. Nothing like that. Oh - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, definitely. Oh my - my - my father 
had a stick on the chair by the side of him all the time, oh yes. Definitely, if you - if you'd forgotten, just had your hand on the table - before you knew where you were that was that - cut with the stick. Never allowed to talk - unless you were spoken 
to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well we had to ask if we wanted to get down, but usually you waited 'til mother and father had finished. All got down together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, all of us, we had a - nice large table, which was a - a scrubbed table. And it really was scrubbed. Beautifully white. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you always have your same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Same places, yes, everyone had the same places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother always serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Me - me mother only served the meal, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did your younger brothers and sisters sit before they were old enough to sit up at the table? How did they go on for feeding then?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they sat - we used to have one chair. Higher chair - for t
hem, always for the younger ones in a high chair, and they sat by the side of mother. She would feed them, yes, the younger ones. And the next younger one would sit next to father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 About how old would they be by the time they could sit up at the table without the high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - about - two and a half. Quite that - perhaps two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was your mother an easy person to get along with, was she easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh my mother was very easy indeed, because my mother never gossiped over a wall
. Never stood - she hadn't got time for anything like that. Never any gossiping. She never had time for any gossiping at all. No, no. And our - house was really - lovely and clean, and our beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was she an affectionate sort of woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Very. You could always go and tell her anything or ask her anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You could share your worries with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you share your worries with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I never used to - go to father for anything. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well we certainly had to respect them. Absolutely. Sunday of course you go to Sunday school in the morning, then you go to Sunday school in the afternoon. And again in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You had to go three times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Three times, yes. Then on a Sunday we used the other room, and my father had special records, which he played, you know you turn the handle with a horn to it those days, cylinder records, the round ones, and you had to sit quiet, y
ou never had to speak when you was listening to the records on the Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of records were they, what sort of music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Very very - select - beautiful stuff, happy records. My father was very fond of church organ - music, and I - I'm very
 musical myself, and I was very fond of it. All very very lovely stuff used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think your liking it results from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think so. Definitely. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Oh yes, we were not allowed to - fight and carry on like that, like some people do, no, not allowed that. No. Mother would bring you together and want to know why, now what is it now? What has he done and what has she done, wan
ts to know all about it. Square it up like that, not - we were never allowed to fight you never saw that in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about as a child outside the family hurt you, would your parents tell you to hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - if it was absolutely
 necessary, not otherwise. Leave other children alone. Come to tell mother if there's anything wrong and she'll go and see - what was wrong to their parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they 
really expected to grow up - better than they were, any rate brought up, which everybody has turned out better - than they were. At our ages any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, certain things had to be very important in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things would they emphasise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well - if anybody was older, you were young - always respect that person or ask if you could help them in any way. Or if there was anybody ill in that house, just go and ask to see if you could do a little job for them, anything like that. Which - often -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So they emphasised neighbourliness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes - but opposite us there was rather a large family there - and - and they used to drink. Especially the man. And the
re was always trouble there. Perhaps father used to - go over there and just square it up. Then - the children used to be crying and mother said, well just go over there and just bring two of them over here. Anything like that. To help in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - terrible. No, not swearing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never heard it in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
My mother and father wouldn't swear in front of us any rate. If they had a - an argument with the two of us, they'd - wait 'til the children were out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, no, no. No. You were only - if mother asked you a question or - your aunt or anybody, then you could speak, but not otherwise, you never joined in anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you ever punished by your mother or just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Very seldom by mother. Very very seldom. I can just - only remember once just having a little tap otherwise but not - father used to have a - the cane, definitely. Good and proper, wasn't just lightly done either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would he punish you very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well once I can remember he went out - and my eldest sister supposed to be looking after us. So I thought to myself, well I think I'll have one or two friends in. Not doing any harm. So we had a 
game moo cows all round the front. In - of course it was grass with a - lovely - patch in the middle with flowers. And we was playing you know, the moo cows all the way round this grass, which I thought was a bit of run, all of a sudden saw father - come 
r
ound the corner. All of us what was doing it had to line up for a jolly good thrashing. These children had to - get out of it quickly, and we all had a jolly good thrashing for that. Well to me - since I've - got older I thought how cruel that was, just f
or innocent game. In your own garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of it at the time, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well I thought at the time when he was - giving us the thrashing - waiting after one had one and one had the other, I thought it was terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He'd use the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh definitely. Definitely. And you had it naked on your be - on your seat. Yes. Of course since - I've grown I've thought how cruel that is. For an innocent game like that. In - inside your own garden. Just because we was all calling o
ut moo, calling moo cows that's all. To me that was a - nothing to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Why do you think your father was so strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think he was brought up rather - from his own family. It came from that side. Yes, because - my grandmother, when I went down on
ce - she said to me, come on, don't lay in bed like that, get out and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 lead the grate. As young as I was I thought - well I haven't come down for that, I thought I'd come down for pea picking - at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You'd gone down for a bit of a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. And come on, get out and - turn your sleeves up and black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 lead the grate. And she said to me, that's not polished enough. She said, there's tuppence, and there's a bottle. She said, and go down to the - and get two pennorth of elbow grease. 
I had to walk three miles there and three miles back. And I went to this - oil shop. And I said, two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
pennorth of elbow grease. He said, my dear child, he said, what your grandmother means - she means you're to use this, plenty of elbow grease with your - h
and and arm. Well I went all the way back home crying. Three miles there and three miles back I walked. Which I thought was terribly cruel. Terribly cruel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you very old at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No, I was about - getting on for twelve. And I've never forgotten it. And I never will forget it. You were just a slave to the - place.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or was one more important than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I respected my mother more than my father. Definitely. I never liked cruelty you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When you had a birthday would that be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, you had a birthday card, yes. Yes. You'd have - have a card which was signed by all the - family. And - posted. And I 
daresay you would have a - a little present of some kind or other. Small but it was - used to be - quite - useful, what you liked. Perhaps it would be a small doll or a set of dolls clothes. Something like that, but we all had - one card, which everybody 
signed it and - and mother posted it, so it come through the post.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you have anything special to eat or any other children in or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, you wouldn't have any children in, but mother would always make a - a plain little cake with some ice on it, for you, yes, and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you had quite a nice birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, that wasn't too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about Christmas Day, can you remember what you did with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Christmas Day we used to han
g our - or the night beforehand, we used to have a stocking given us each. And you - pinned it up, safety pin at the end of the bed. And of course in the middle of the night you used to go down and feel, see if Father Christmas had been. Of course he had 
b
een you see, but we daren't make a noise because - father would be listening, he'd come out straight away. So we knew he'd been then we settled down then you see. 'Til the morning. And - it used to be - what I appreciated the most was - the tuppenny woode
n dolly, in those days. No clothes on. Just the tuppenny little wooden dolly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 These were the wooden joint }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12732631\charrsid479496 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. And an orange. One apple. A few nuts. And some - money, wraped up in - gold money, chocolate, and a sugar mouse. And perhaps
 a little trumpet or something like that used to be or a little mouth organ. And - always the bag of little tiny biscuits with a little piece of sugar on the top of those, used to be a bagful of those, inside the stacking. Well that's about all you had. N
ear Christmas. And I - I carried that stocking about all Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any games or anything like that Christmas Day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, there wouldn't be any games. There'd just - just be some extra records which you could - perhaps have a littl
e sing - with them, they wouldn't be the - records, Jack and Jill and all things like that would be then. Then you would have this - if you'd been - been good all day long you'd have hot - whatever you - look - well likely you was asked - if you'd like a 
b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14953832\charrsid479496 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
ackcurrant hot drink or a - peppermint hot drink. You had that, you know, and you had - oranges and apples - in the meantime to buy the apples - and oranges and nuts we had to go out carol singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You had to get the money for those did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Ha
d to get the money for the oranges, nuts and apples. One house we went to my sister and I - and that was in the Grove, Muswell Hill, one house there was having a - party. It was a children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14953832\charrsid479496 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s party, one of their birthdays. We were singing these Christmas ca
rols outside, you know, we kept knocking at the door. So they - let us sing another carol then they opened the door. And they said, come in. So we went in. And they said, are you thirsty? So we said, yes. Especially I was - I was very thirsty. So they ask
e
d what we would like to drink. We'd like some milk or would we like an orange drink or a lemon drink or a grapefruit drink, or what they'd got, well we had this drink, I for - I - I think it was an orange drink we had, and they said, would you like a piec
e
 of the cake? So we said yes please. So we had that. We were sat down. Then they said, now, after you've had that we would like you to sing two carols and they stood us up on a chair. There was rather a lot - there. And we sung these carols to them. And -
 
they thanked us very much, and they gave us a bagful of - oranges and nuts and - biscuits, and a bag of sweets for our - selves, I said this was for our parents - the nuts and that were, they gave us a half a crown each. But we never went to any other hou
se, we simply tore home like mad with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was a larger house or a wealthy house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Very wealthy house and a very nice house it was, very. And - I've never forgotten that in my life. Because sometimes you see if you go out - carol sing
ing sometimes they send the dog after you, anything like that. But - that was done - very - most unusual. You - we usually - used to do very very well with carol singing, 'cos we - used to go to the best - houses and - you know, used to get sixpence or a 
s
hilling and some of them would give you - one or two sweets to eat or - we used to have them ourselves of course, never took those home. We only took the money home. But this one place they asked us in which I've never forgotten. And I know that house now
 and that's still there. Muswell Hill, The Grove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any musical instruments in the house, you had the gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14953832\charrsid479496 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 phone, but did you have anything you played yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We only - mouth organ and - what - what - what's those - flute. One of those.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who played those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Brother. And I tried a - you know, with a mouth organ and that and me other sister did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents play any instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They never used to play any instruments, no, my father was very very fond of the - g
ramophone records. He used to be a choirboy when he was younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever make music together as a family? Did you have a sing-song?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, used to - used to have a - a sing, yes. Yes, we could sing at Christmas time, especially the carols 
father wanted us all to sing. Yes, and the best one used to get - an extra - sweet or something like that, you had something extra. Oh and postman's knock we used to play, that's right, at Christmas time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about other times of the year, would your parents play any games with you, winter evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not as a rule, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, we had some books in the house, which - people used to give us. Books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of books were these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Like Minnie M
ouse in books and things like that. One was called our Winnie which I - got from Sunday school, and that, used to pass it round the family, and especially if they won a book as well. Children\rquote s books, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any magazines or newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Father used to - always have the People. Every Sunday had the People, wouldn't miss that for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he have a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I never can remember a daily paper coming, only the People.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever read out loud to the family or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I never heard them read out to fam - the family, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Can you remember a funeral in the family or can you remember going to a funeral before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, I never went to a funeral. No. Not - not before - father died in 1927. No, I never went to a funeral. I'd seen the - little baby opposite - the funeral from - that, but I never went to it but I saw it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 About how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I shoul
d say somewhere about ten. And I - was very upset about that. Dried - it died of convers - convulsions. Father tried his hardest, he - he was very good like that. Yes. To see if he could survive the - the baby, but he couldn't. And - once - on - this was 
o
n a Sunday, father was very good then. There was a little tiny - space ground where the - horses and carts used to go up, there was a - public house at the top of there, and used to get stuck in the mud sometimes in the winter, these horses, and - childre
n
 made a - fire up there on this piece of ground, one Sunday morning, and one child got pushed - pushed right onto the fire. And they just shouted for my father. Father went and wrapped this child up in - blanket and that and cut all her - clothes off and 
t
hat, off her. Apparently when the ambulance came - the ambulance men said to father that you've saved this child's life. He done all - he could for her face was all burnt, father done all what he could for her, and she's still alive today but she's just s
c
arred all round the mouth and that. And I always remember that, him cutting her boots and - clothes off of her, he cut off. If there was any trouble in the street, anybody got cuts or - knocked down, they'd always come - to fa - my father for that. And he
'll treat them, he was very good like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Why do you think that was, because the doctor's surgery was in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I - I - I don't know whether - he never touched his things. He had - my father had his own - things you see 'cos - as I say he u
sed to have - take these photographs and he snapped that. And I don't know - but - he certainly was very - he was very respected in the street, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives at all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
I've never been taken out by my mother and father all the time we lived there. No. The only outings we had - is when we had our Sunday school outing, we went on brakes, horses, four horses, and you had your Sunday school outing, or - any other, perhaps th
ey'd pick - two or three out of our house for a little extra treat to go to Hadleigh Woods, with the brakes. And that was all - paid for, but we've never been out once with me mother and father, as children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did - they take you out shopping or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, never - never once did I got out shopping with me mother and father, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about Bank Holidays when you were a child, what would happen on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Bank Holidays they'd give you a bagful of sandwiches - and you'd 
- and a bottle of; lemonade, which they made themselves, cut up from the lemons, and filled two or three bottles and you had to stop up the Palace, 'cos it was lovely then, 'cos we lived near the Palace, it was very nice up there then you could slide down
 
the bank and do what you like, and we thoroughly enjoyed our eats because you could do what you liked with them then, could eat them before time or - just have a jolly good time with your friends, for the day, but we was never - in the house, holiday time
s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would your parents do on a Bank Holiday then, would they go out or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh no, they wouldn't go out, no. Long as they got rid of us, that's all they wanted. Perhaps they might do a little bit of decorating. While we're out the way. 'Cos - they all done the dec - mother and father always done the decorating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever go away for a holiday when you were a child? You said you went to your gran's once for pea-picking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Went to the - went to me - always used to go to me grandmother's, or one of my aunts. Which they had a paper shop, and a toy shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was that in Grays area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In Grayssend, near Tunbridge Wells, yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Gravesend{\*\xmlclose}
, yes. And I can remember walking round this shop - and - me aunt brought me a little - it was a litt
le coat, blue coat, and it'd got a cape to it, and it was lined with - yellow underneath, silk, nice, and I should like to just flap it back to show off with it. Then I had one of the largest dolls which was wax those days. Wax dolls. Do - do you ever kno
w
 of a Wax doll? Auntie gave me a wax doll. Which of course you mustn't keep in the sun too long 'cos it would melt. And I treasured this wax doll what she gave me, and this - it was navy blue - and - some embroidery round this cape. And I came home all - 
very posh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How often would you go away to one of your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well, it might be perhaps once in two years, three years, that's all. Never any more than that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long would you stay when you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh we'd stay for week or a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would any of the other members of the family go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, you only went one at a time. Only one at a time, work it like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things would you do on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well she used to take us out, different places, yes. I 
think there was a little zoo there, we'd - go and see that and - take us out for little rides and - quite a - high time in your life. And - you know you're not going to have it again for another three or four years. And I thoroughly enjoyed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about your holiday with your gran?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well, with her you see it wasn't quite so good, she - liked you to work, so we used to have to go in the fields and help to pea - picking, you know. It used to give you a little bit of money for pea-picking, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was at Grays was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. Yes. I used to enjoy it but - I used to want to do what I wanted to do really you see. I didn't think I'd gone down there to black-lead the stove and things like that. I thought I'd gone down just to - for 
- help with the pea picking which I thoroughly enjoyed putting the sacks and you tie them up. It was - it was lovely. It was a change from being home any rate. And having your three slices, 'cos I had more down there. If you wanted more I used to ask for 
it and I had it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about your weekends when you were a child, how would you spend your Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh I used to go doorstep cleaning when on - Sat - Saturdays, I worked - the whole day. The whole day, I worked doorstep cleaning in the mornin
g and then I went to take out babies in the afternoon. I had one very - permanent job of a Saturday afternoon to take - two babies out. And that was from about - half past two - 'til about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past five{\*\xmlclose}. And then they'd give me me tea. And there used to b
e - sixpence or something like that they'd give - perhaps they used to give me an apple. And that used to be good. I used to like that. That used to be something I different than having just three slices of bread when you went home. But the money what you
 earnt - you see, always gave it up. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you get any of that back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well you might get a penny or tuppence you see and that's put in your box. But you only had a penny a week to spend. If -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You weren't allowed to spend this other money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No. No. You only allowed one penny a week to spend, mind you those days you'd get four ounces of sweets for a penny. See, a farthing went a - a long way. See, you could get a nice strip of liquorice for a farthing, you know, roll it up you see and t
ake a piece off and that would last you - you know, and these - faggots. Tiger nuts and that used to get you see, you - perhaps you don't know anything about tiger nuts. Get a bagful of tiger nuts for a farthing. Beautiful. Lovely MacKintosh's toffee, fou
r ounces a penny. Ooh, I can taste it now. Real - MacKintosh's toffee. Mm. Not made today like it, oh no. No. It isn't. MacKintosh's toffee whatever they call it's - not the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would happen to the money that went in your moneybox then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Ah
 then they would buy me a pair of shoes. They'd got to buy me a pair of shoes or - if I wanted a coat. See, mother'd buy me a pair of shoes or a coat, or - or a hat or - perhaps a dress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Special c
lothes for Sunday, they was taken off directly you came in. See, or - perhaps if anybody was to call on a Sunday - then you just put a - pinafore on. See? Then - when your aunt or anybody had knocked at the door you go upstairs and take your pinafore off.
 So they didn't see you with a pinafore on. But we always had pinafores. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 My father would never let us play on a Sunday, once - I' just washed a pair of stockings out and put the
m on the line, he just cut the line down. Never allowed anything like that on a Sunday, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yet he didn't mind you going baby minding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not on a Sunday. No. I never used to mind the babies, I used to go and see if anybody had got one so I could g
o and show it off to mother and father, somebody's got a new baby. Never used to go out to - wheel 'em out or mind them, no, not on - not on a Sunday. Saturdays or any other day of the week, but not Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would they go every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Not every Sunday, no. No. When there was anything special on - they would come, especially when there was prize giving, they would like to see what we are going to get. Then they used to come and be very pleased with us then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What denomination were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you attend Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, because my school was a - a Church of England school as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you just used to go to the Sunday school or did you go to the church services with your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, never went - to - a church service with mother and father. Only went to the church, the - Sunday school - by ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How often did your father go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 My father very - seldom went to a church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother go at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Seldomly - when the baby was christened, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But they'd more or less just go for things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Just like that, that was all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things would happen on these or where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Hadleigh Woods. We went once to Southend. Those days used to go on the brakes, you know, with four horses - drawing you along. And you took your - lunch with you. And usually you h
ad a little bit of money, and of course when you got there you usually spent it all at once, buying presents for your mother and father and - cornets and things for yourself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The trip to Southend would be by train would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any other social activities organised by the church, or any that you took part in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Now let me see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about a choir, did you belong to a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, I was always in the - the choir, I always used to sing, and practically someth
ing every Sunday morning, my sister and I. I was very interested in singing all - I - I've always been - that - like that all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they have a separate choir or was this part of the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, part of the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the church run a temperance club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, they never done one of those, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any other clubs organised by a church or chapel that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Some they called - a guild.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well you could go to that and you could - learn one or two things, or they have a speaker there, for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this while you were a schoolgirl or later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, when I was at school. Yes. Go in the evening. When you got - a little older you see. That was for the evenings
. That used to be quite interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well we never used to do it ourselves, we used to have somebody to come in and speak to us about all lots of different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Like travel lectures or temperance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Something like that, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, grace always was said at meals. We said, for what you was going to receive the Lord make you truly thankful, amen. If you said, for what you had received - you got dow
n from the table and you had nothing at all. 'Cos my father said your mind wasn't on what you were going to do. Your mind was on playing and that's all. He's very very strict like that my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever have family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, we ne - never had family prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 To say prayers at night, yes, always had to kneel by the side of the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your father take any interest in politics do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. He was a very - Conservative man. Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you know why he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, he never used to talk about politics but he always - well - well you could hear him with mother you know always talking about the Conservative people, but he would never vote for anyth
ing else but Conservative. And he did say once I can remember that when you grow up, he said, I want you to follow in my footsteps. To think about the Conservatives and not anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their jo
bs or their house if they voted differently from their employer, do you know if your father was ever under that sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, he thought about police, he was very fond of helping in the police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he do any work at election times for the parties or would he just vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, he'd just vote for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, me mother was a rank Conservative. Absolutely yes. Yes, they used to go together then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When your parents were not working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well I'm afraid my mother was - always working, I mean she never had any leisure time whatever. And father, when he - had any leisure time at all he used to do photography. P
erhaps there used to be somebody wanted - a wedding taken, the groups. Go to a wedding. Or - a funeral, take the - photograph of the grave. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He used to develop these at home did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Develop these at home. Which - were - the old 
time developing was you'd put them on the window sill so they - coloured like that. Time them. In sepia you know, you don't see sepia these days, just black and white and coloured. YES. Yes. Then he used to - develop them in the bath. And we used to have 
to go upstairs to see if they was - running round and doing all right. I took a great interest in that as well. Yes, in photography, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You helped him with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. And - when they were ready you see, half a dozen at a time, people used to orde
r them you see, you used to take them round the houses and get the money for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I suppose this was a fairly profitable sideline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes it was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother have an interest outside the home? Did she ever go to church guild or any of those sort of evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She never had any time for anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She never went out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not at all my mother, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many evenings a week would your father spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I should say majority of evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He didn't go out too much then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, my father would - never went out. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he belong to any clubs or would he go out for a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 None whatever. Oh my father would never go in a pub in his life. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He resented drink on principle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Absolutely a tee-totaler my father. He would never have anything like that in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about gambling, would he have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, nothing like that, no. Nothing like that. The things we used to play - was havi
ng a game of patience. Or dominies. He used to like anything like that, but there was no money ever in our family, in the way of gambling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well he used to be interested in football, you know, he used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would he go to a football match?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, he wouldn't go to one. He'd be - he'd follow it up, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know whether your father or mother belonged to any savings clubs, boots clubs or sick clubs, these sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well my - mother used to pay in for a - a club for clothing for - for the children. But nothing - nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this at a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, a man call - come round at the door. Like they call a - a - tallyman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh very well indeed, lovely. They used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Is there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Cecil. He was the one I was passionately fond of. We used to have a game if father was out - any time - and especially if we went upstairs and laid on
 our bed they - he'll bring the mattress down with us, all the way down the stairs and put us out the back garden, lock the door so you couldn't get in. That's the tricks they used to play on us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who did you play with as a child? Was it mainly your brothers and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No neighbours friends I had - two special friends of - of girls, and that's one of them had the soup kitchen, when we used to go round and get - a jug of soup, free. We had - had a ticket - from the school, and we'd
 go and get this jug of soup, for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this a small shop or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, it was a house. And they made this soup in the copper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Why was it made in a private house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - these people volunteered you see to do it. Fo
r the council. That was all done by the council. Yes. They was paid - so much you see for doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say you were never allowed to play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never allowed to play in the street, no. No, any time -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there a park or anywhere like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Alexandra{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceName}}Palace{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was the nearest to - us, where we could go and play up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You could go there in the evenings or any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, Sat - no - no, we could never go out to play on a Saturday, or in the evenings. The only time we p
layed up the Palace was when we had holidays - from school. Other times on - Saturdays, we had to work. I had my doorstep cleaning to do and brass cleaning and - a child to take out and - was always a job to do at home you see in the evenings, when we had
 this doctor's surgery - there was always the medicine to take out. Mother used to take in his washing, and - she'd finished it and ironed it, and that had got to be delivered. We didn't get much - we never got much time for playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well I can always remember - tipping the cigarette pictures. Tippings we used to call that. I was very fond of that. Then we had - hoops in those days, land the boys had iron hoops, in those days, which you could play - with. Not in th
e streets. But you can play them quite easily and safely. Marbles, I was very fond of marbles. And five stones. I was very good at five stones. Yes, loved that. And me brothers was interested in that too, the five stones, and they'd have a game of marbles
 with you. Sit outside in the - back garden, you could play for hours like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. As long as we cleaned ourselves, oh yes, we could get dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased or did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, could play who you pleased.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any or did you belong to any youth organisations at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It's what - they - I forget they - what they used to call it those days, something like the - Girls Cubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The Girl Guides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Guides things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You belonged to those did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. To go - for Sunday school, you see, then you used to go on a - Monday, sometimes on a Friday. Only was fo
r about - half an hour or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no uniform we had those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have a badge or anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, I had a badge. You used to wear a skirt, and a blouse as a rule. To go in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any hobbies then, did you collect things or do any gardening, any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, I was fond of gardening if I was allowed to do it. You could - you - everybody in the house - child had their own little patch in the back garden. And you could plant what 
you liked in that, it was all measured out, father used to do that. Measure it out for you. Then - he'd give you a packet of seeds, and he would see which was the best one could - grow, and those who was the best - of course you usually had a extra penny 
that week, then he'd take the photograph of that little patch, with you standing by it. Yes, I was very interested in garden. Mother and father was too. Used to grow a few cabbages and - tomatoes and - little odd things like that, lettuces. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Your father was quite strict but he did take quite an interest in what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
He'd - yes, he took an interest in what we done, yes. He had a shed out in the garden you see, 'cos he always used to ride a bike, and - two of my brothers usually used to go out riding with father. Used to go right out Barnet way and 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}South Mimms{\*\xmlclose}, places like that. Used to enjoy that they did, with father riding the bike. The girls never had a bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would they go for a day or something like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. The girls never had a bike. We had a pram. We always had a pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you given the choice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, it was usually a - wasn't a new pram we had or - never a new pram. Some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to choose between a bicycle and a pram?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no, no, we nev
er had - the girls never - was asked if we'd like a bike, no, and of course I would never go on a bike, I was too nervous. Yes. It didn't matter at all. I didn't mind if they made - a - a - plank and put four wheels on it. And the boy - used to pull you a
long on it down the - hill, I used to like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you take part in any sports as a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Racing. Won twice. In racing we had that at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Friday
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. That's at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}North Finchley{\*\xmlclose}. That's where we used to have our races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this with the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
For the school. Yes. And I always remember winning a - doll's tea set, and a skipping rope. Asked you which you would like, so I said a - doll's \endash  tea set and a skipping rope. I was fond of doing the salt, mustard, and vinegar - pepper, they don't 
do that today you see. It's different. Hopscotch. That was all different - those days to what it is today. Yes. Different altogether. Used to make a round ring. They don't do that today. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about things like concerts or music hall or cinemas while you were still at school, do you remember things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, we never went to pictures. In those days there was - only talking pictures wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You mean silent pictures?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Silent pictures. The thing we used to have at home was a
 magic lantern done by father. And we all used to sit on the stairs. One on top - right to the top and father had the screen - in the hall, 'cos it wasn't a very large hall those days you know, narrow, but he could manage to put the - screen there, and we
 used to have this magic lantern - now and again, and that was real good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you didn't go to the theatre or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. Father used to do this - magic lantern for us. That was a real treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you get regular pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Always had your pocket money on Saturdays. Regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How much was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Penny. Yes. Penny. Unless you won - anything else you see, you - done anything different and perhaps you'd have - have - have another extra penny. Then of course if you d
id - get the money for - doing a job for anybody, you put it in the box. You - everybody had a box, which was a pillar box in those days, a red pillar-box, you know, and sometimes if you feel as though you wanted a hapenny out you know used to try and get
 it out with a knife but you got caught with it was a rule. It was found out you had a jolly good hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If you earnt a shilling or whatever cleaning doorsteps would you be allowed to have any of that or would it all have to go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That - all of that mother - my - gave that to mother. That all went to mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or her family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, some of the other - girls used to, younger ones used to help, we'd wipe up or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But anyone apart from family, any neighbours or relatives, people like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh no, no, no, we done everything ourselves. No neighbours ever helped - us, we helped them. There was lots of poor people round where were. And we helped them, they needed help - perhaps more than what we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about if your mother was ill or when she was confined to bed with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh that wasn't long. She was soon up and about again. In those days. No, we all done for ourselves. Each one - had to do somet
hing. And father was there to see that we done it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would father help at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He would go - he would help then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, not nearby at all, we never had anybody - living nearby. One in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and Tunbridge Wells and - further way - further afield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So did you see anything of your relatives when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Sometimes, yes, not very often though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It'd be more or less a holiday would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about friends, did your parents have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not many friends in, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there anyone that used to come round visiting them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well, only one used to come round visiting was the - one from the school if you hadn'
t gone that day to school you see. It's - way - the school board - when mother was ill, and had a baby, one of us had got to stop home - from school you see, then the back - the school board'd come round and see why you hadn't gone to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They wouldn't have like friends call round, were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes if you - now and again you could have somebody in to tea because they - a friend would ask you to tea, you said, mother and father, could - a friend of mine's - asked
 me to tea and could I go, and they would say yes. And - I used to ask could I have her back again to tea. It wasn't often, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about their own friends though, would they invite any friends at all, your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We very seldom ha
d any friends in the house whatever. My - my mother and father was not one of these people - would have - gossip or anything like that, they never had time for that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They were fairly self-contained were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Many people
 divide society into different social classes or groups. At that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another? Were you conscious of social divisions in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I felt as though we should have done some
thing. I wanted to do - dressmaking and - you had to pay for it in those days you see if you wanted to learn anything. But any rate I did go and - to - cookery lessons. I was very fond of that. We didn't have it at the school you see, you had to go furthe
r away for that, over Friern Barnet way. Yes. And you could bring it home, what you cooked. And have a little, you know, little dib in and have a little lick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You used to do this extra from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 From school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say there were a lot of poorer people in the neighbourhood, and you said there were some areas of richer people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, that were at Muswell Hill, the top of Muswell Hill. We were down at the bottom you see. That was a poorer place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many social groups would you say there were at that time before 1918? How would you divide society at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Small I'd say. Those days. Small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would you say they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Band of Hope. That's what I remember. And I used to go to the Band of Hope. That - that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That was with the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No. That was on a Saturday night. And that used to be very enjoyable, this Band of Hope. And you could have a sing-song and you could have a dance. And - that - that was always called the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this while you were at school or afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Just when I'd left school. Mm. Yes. That had been going on for some time though and I'd always wanted to go to that when I was about ten. But they said you couldn't go, not yet a while but you will be able to 
go when you get just a little bit older. But you never hear of Band of Hope now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What was it formed for, do you remember what the Band of Hope was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was to get you - together so you could dance and sing or - different things like that, social - evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 These poorer people, what sort of occupations would they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well they wouldn't have much occupations because their father was always coming home drunk. And they was always being fighting. You could always hear the children screaming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you think the class was more a matter of the way people behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Definitely the way the people behaved, yes, some of them it was really terrible. Some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would you call those sort of families, would you call them working class or poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, the poor, they wouldn't think of - you know, they wanted somebody to do something for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would you say is the next social group above them or the next one in the scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well the next - were - some of them go out to work you see, like we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would you call that class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well I call them - second class. And the poor - then - a little bit higher up you see, the second class I'd call them. That's what they was called. Those days And - when you go further up you see then there's the - rather we call the rich people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So there's more or less three classes you'd say would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Very poor. Indeed, 'cos you saw some of the children running about with not a thing on their feet, and hardly dressed at all.
 Because what we had left off - and ours weren't always new, mother used to say, go round and take that to Mrs Bishop, that was her name, the husband was always coming home drunk there. Was always fighting and carrying on going on there. And we felt sorry
 
for the children, 'cos there was about - twelve to fourteen of them. One family, down a little further, had twenty-two children. And they were very poor. And we used to try and help them - in different ways. Perhaps if we'd had a parcel from - one of my a
unts - then we could cast off some of our clothes you see and mother'd make up a little parcel and send it down to them. 'Cos they really needed it. There wasn't all this welfare business like there is today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 There was - some of 'em are very nice people indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of occupations would you say they were mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well help in butchers shops and things like that. Shop assistants, yes. But - delivering coal, coalmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What about what class person would you say for example a railway worker was in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well that was pretty good, if they was a railway worker in those days, yes. Yes, because - they could go on a train. If their father was - working on the railway. That would be pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about shopkeepers, what class would you say they were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh shopkeepers those days were very very good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say they were your class or rich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they were - better class than what we were. But they used to be pretty good to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you consider them in the rich class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, I should say so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Teachers? Well - if - you just came in late -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I mean as regards class, which class would you say they were in in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I - I think they were very very good teachers because they had forty to fifty in a class. And that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say they were in your class or the rich class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, the richer class. Yes. Yes. There was always - fifty and sometimes sixty in a class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who do you think people like shopkeepers and teachers mixed with when they weren't at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I don't really know what - who they mixed with but I should think - they mixed more with their own - class. Teache
rs, 'cos they used to study you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Do you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another, were you ever taught to curtsey to certain people or things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh my father always said yes, respect - people who was - better than yourself. He always said that. And to speak properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You mean better class persons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, a better class person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you taught to call anyone madam or sir and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No. Only at school, the - with the master, yes sir, and no sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way, calling them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the district you lived in who were considered the most important people in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
I think the milkman really. Yes, when he caused to come round with the can, used to - you never had milk left at your doorsteps in those days, he came round with a big - can, scooped it out, pints or half a pints. He was very well respected he was
. And the greengrocer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So this would be mainly the local shop people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Shop - shop people, local shop people, important people they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Quite respectable people. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they were good, yes. They were very good - chapel people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you notice any different in the class between the two or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well you - knew the way how they dressed better of course. To a poor - to the poorer peop
le you knew they dressed much better than you did. See and they would give more money than you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You mean the poor people didn't go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, the - the - the poor people would go to the churches. But you would see the difference with the dress. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you notice any difference between church people and chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well I always think chapel people were more friendly than the church people. Far more friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You think there'd be more richer people or less richer people at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well those days you see when the people went to the church, the Church of England - they used to come from Muswell Hill, and they were really - people who'd got money, because they had servants. And they were really - nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh chapel people will be - different to what those kind of people were. You know, speak different and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Poorer or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, poorer in dress. Could always see a lady - from Muswell Hill to what you could a - from one further down 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Coneyhatch Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. They was dressed much different, oh and spoke different of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you think one lot would go to the church and the other to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, they wouldn't do that, not for - the Muswell Hill people wouldn't. They wouldn't go to the chapel. They'd keep to their church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or did it vary quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh it varied. Yes, varied quite a bit. Yes, I can reme
mber my mother sometimes when this big family - letting us take a - bread pudding round there to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you know what sort of occupation their father had?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well he was a drunkard. Absolutely a drunkard. And the mother had so many children that she just couldn't know what to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They were very rough some, very very rough. Very rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think one group in the working class felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In what ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well we've had - felt more superior than the other people did. And our house was kept better for one thing, I mean our windows looked better, my mother was very particular with her curtains up at the window, and our wind
ows was always kept nice and clean. Our hedge all round was all nicely kept clipped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So one important thing would have been neatness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Neatness, oh very. Well we had to be for one thing, 'cos we had - I told you this doctor's surgery there. And our -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of other differences would there be between rough and respectable families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Rough would be playing out - chalk all outside the place and all over the wall of their place, all like that. We never had any chalk - outside our house, never. The windows and that never looked clean. Curtains filthy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would she consider herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well con she - she - she considered herself bett
er than like the person next door. For one thing, 'cos we had one net door to us what was - pretty rough. She classed herself much higher than that, and she dressed herself - nice, my mother always looked very clean and tidy. - And my mother had beautiful
 hair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would she consider herself working class or middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, she was a proper working class person, she worked very hard. We had a lot to be thankful for for our mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was it possible at that time to move from one social class to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, you never moved about. No. You stopped where you were, you never used to move about those days. 'Cos we had a whole house - then, and it was only ten shillings a week the rent. That you would never get ten shillings a week rent today for
 a whole house would you? Three bedrooms, we know it was small and the other rooms were small but it was a whole house for ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social groups or do you think they had different attitudes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
They used to - respect people, I mean talk to them if they'd got any trouble they'd try and see if they could - sort if out for them. See when there was a terrible row over the other side of the road one - two or three of the children
 would come running over to our house and we'd try and sort it out for them. Not the children, we wouldn't, but mother and father would try and - see what they could do, bring the children into our place for a little while. And they'd try and talk to them
.
 See if they could sort them down, 'cos they keep fighting with one another. Father was very good like that. It's - 'cos he belonged to - a special constable. And - he was - he was called out quite a lot of times - for - street rowing and fighting. You kn
ow, in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They'd come to him because they knew he was a special constable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. Yes. That's what it was. You see - see the mothers being thrown out - or down the stairs. Yes, those days. It was terrible. They was always having black eyes, the woman - opposite us, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the street you lived how many respectable families were there and how many rough ones would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well I should say more respectable than - than not. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Yes. Used to see a po - I used to say to him, I've been very good today. He said, you sure you have? I said, yes. I've been very good up to now. He said, keep it up then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of the police in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh I loved the police. Yes, because - really - we had a police come round on horseback which you never see today. And it was lovely to hear that horse clop round the stop outside our house. Wanted to - to see father about something, and t
his house would stop outside our house. And we'd always have a lot of children come round then, to see this police stopping outside - Shipman's house, that was our name. Yes, must go round and see the - this horse, see what they're therefore
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How do you think the police treated people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Pretty good. Yes, pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Your home was rented, did you see anything of your landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Never saw anything - any of our landlords, no. No. Every week - the rent man would call but you never saw the rent man - himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of the landlord, was he a good one or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well he could have done more for - more for us. Which he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He didn't look after the place much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. We looked after it ourselv
es. Even I - used to - do a little bit of whitewashing. I used to say my mother, can I whitewash the toilet the out? She said, yes, you - you can do that, do you want to do any painting? I said, yes please. Father used to be pleased if we would help - do 
a
nything like that and then he would let us. He'd tie something round us right up to round our necks. And give us - it used to be whitewash those days in a bucket. So we used to enjoy that. Especially if we could do our own room out. He didn't mind - yes. 
He used to cover the - whole bed over with a - things, he said, if you - like to do that, you - you have a go at it. If anyone'd like to do a little bit of painting round, paint your door or paint your window sill, he'll give you some paint and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So he used to encourage your activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Used to encourage us, whatever we wanted to do. Though he was very very strict, he encouraged us what we wanted to do, he never like - although he didn't like - work - going out to work so much himself, he liked to see us do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember as a child feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You were aware of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I was aware of it, oh yes. That's why I didn't mind going out and doing - something to bring some money in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of this at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well I thought it was pretty terrible at the time. That a certain wage wasn't coming into the house. Like when you go to school you hear - your other friends saying oh - my mother
 - had so and so - given to her. What did your mother have? I said, my mother didn't have anything given to her, my father didn't give her anything this week. So I don't know how we're going to pay the rent. Things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How often was your father out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, a good many times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did it make a noticeable difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, because you see the - every shop didn't want sign-writing done did they, and a name over a shop many times did they. So - and - he - done a little photograph in you see to make up, and - there wasn't people what wanted a lot of those in that day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We never got anything those days, in the par - from the parish, no. No. Not
 like today. Is it welfare today if you're pay, you - well you get something don't you. But not those days. No sometimes we used to be hungry. Yes. And - we didn't used to tell mother and father but somebody used to give us a ha'penny, well we'd get a hap
porth of Tottenham cake, that used to be gorgeous in those days. It really was - Tottenham cake, it was a nice piece of ice on the top, big slice. Plain sponge cake, it was Tottenham cake used to call it. Cor. Beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If there was someone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they used to - you know, well we'll see if we could get them out of the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How would you get about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well different people used to
 say, let's see if we can get them out the way, they're causing too much trouble in the - neighbourhood. And they - used to want so many people to - organise things - sign things and see if we can get them out of the way. Sometimes we did, sometimes we di
dn't get them out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If they signed something who would they give it to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think they go to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Friern{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Barnet{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Town Hall{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever take the law into their own hands, some people have told us about a thing called rough music wher
e the neighbours, if they want to get rid of someone just as you've describe, they would gather round at night and bash tins.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Bash things - about. Dustbin lids about. YES. All kinds of things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You remember that happening do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes I do. We never took part in that but - we used to see the other boys and - girls doing it, the rough lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Can you tell us what you know about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Used to get - dustbin lids and all kinds of things. Bash 'em about outside their houses
 and - knock the doors about and - sing and shout outside the places. Real rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who would do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The - the youngsters, the boys and - some of the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This would be to get rid of a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. They'd annoyed other people so these others used to annoy them at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you think their parents encourage them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, oh definitely encouraged them to do it, see if we can get rid of them, and they often used to have to go as well. Just so - really - some of those you see
 were really dirty. Well what we used to call - lousy. You don't hear of that now, these days. They really were and course other people - children, used to catch it. You see, and it spread terribly. Lice those days. Shocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember the grown ups ever taking part in these sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, I've seen 'em come out in the street and have a good fight. In the middle of the street. Perhaps a dozen of them, perhaps more. Yes, those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This would be to get rid of a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. 'Course and I used to stand and enjoy it. I used to think that was a bit of fun. But of course it wasn't though. Yes. It was to me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you given any lessons by one of your parents or anyone at all before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well sometim
es father - he was very fond of shorthand and typing. Father used to try and see if he could get one of us to - learn how - shorthand.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That seems very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Three and I loved it
. The very first thing I remember, it was - go - dancing round the maypole, holding my ribbon, dancing round the maypole and tying it up, I can remember that as though it was yesterday. And I loved it. I skipped and hopped and - sung with it and it was - 
glorious. It was - it was just over the road. From our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you didn't have far to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Went at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, well we had to be in school by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock
{\*\xmlclose}, and finish at twelve. Back again at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 14}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}two o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}Half past four{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you start straight away a full day at three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Never came home, that was the full day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What kind of school was it, a church school, was it mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And - that - first starting that was ordinary school. It was mixed, girls and boys, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Board school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. The other school you see you went up - to the - bigger school, that was in the next road, it's a bit further up, t
hat was when you was five. And that was a mixed school. But it was connected with this church. And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
when it was Easter time and other different times you all marched - in the street - to go to the church. And you had a service in there and singing and - it 
was really wonderful. And you came out and marched all down the street again, all people watching you, then you went into school again. I used to love those times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You went there at five?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So this first one you say was a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Child school. Kindergarten or whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And it was run by the local authority?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many children were there, do you remember at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What, when I was three? Oh I should - a hundred or more. Yes. Large playground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about this school you went to at five, how later was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh that was very large. That's when you had fifty and sixty in a class. Boys and girls mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the hours there, were they about the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. It was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} you had to be into school, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}twelve o'clock
{\*\xmlclose} outside. And run home to dinner you see and you'd got one or two jobs to do, then you had to line up in the playground you see to march in. You see, perhaps I wanted to polish me shoes up 'cos I used to like to t
he leader. And I said to mother, could I have a little bit of fresh hair ribbon on. She said, you've had it - clean on this morning, so I said, well I'd better have another piece on, 'cos I'd like to swank - to march the class in. All used to mar - all in
 the playground you see, marched in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you a monitor or prefect or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of the first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I liked school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you like the teachers, how did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well one or two I 
liked better than others, Miss Duck was - I used to call quack quack, she was very strict you know. If you just come that second late and perhaps I'd just done a job, you had the cane for that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They caned the girls as well did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Caned 
the girls as well as the boys. The teachers done that theirselves, you never went out to the master to do that kind of thing. Teachers done that. You always had the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they cane you very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well there was always somebody caned every day. Every day in your class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say you got the cane for talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, oh yes. And perhaps - perhaps somebody in the next - seat to me, the girl - might give me a sweet or perhaps an orange you see. Of course we used to forget in those day
s you see that an orange smelt, see and the teacher could smell it. See, perhaps we'd, you know, peel it under the desk and that and - she used to give me a piece. So of course we never used to won up who'd done it, who's got the orange until she used to 
come round and find out. And you had the cane for that all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they give any other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, used to stay in late - from school. Not in the day - in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}, because they wanted you home for your dinner, but after school time
. Perhaps you had to stop in for an hour - perhaps write out a hundred or two hundred words.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say about polishing your shoes at lunch time, things like this, did the teachers emphasise these sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, it was me father. My father was
 very very particular on cleaning your shoes. And he said, you don't just clean your shoes at the top, and round the heel, he said, you clean under there as well. He said, the underneath part shows just as well as the top. So every day we had to - show my
 father - and we used to have to clean our father's shoes every day. And so you could see your face in them. We were very proud of our shoes. Matter of fact there was always top in the class - I was, for me shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You'd get marks for clean shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Marks for clean shoes, once the teacher said well - we'll take Winnie's shoes off and we - you can see - how she cleans them underneath. Mind you, I was very particular meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So the teachers would be quite fussy about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Fussy about your shoes being cleaned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there other things like this they were fussy about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, if you got nice hair ribbon and different things like that, if you looked nice. Some of them looked very scruffy, as though they wanted a - hair ribbon - washed. 
Perhaps they've had it on about a fortnight, same old - ribbon. And - shoes perhaps have - well just - the front of them and the backs have never been touched. She was very very particular on your shoes. And the way you looked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about things like manners of ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, she - used to like you speaking very - yes, yes miss, that - not - not just yes. Call her by her name. She said, you've got a name, and everybody's got a name, so everybody - likes to be called - by their name. Which was quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Yes, we showed - I used to hurry up home to - show father or mother what I'd done. Especially needlework, if I'd just finished a petticoat or a - used to wear pin
afores in those days always. And we all used to make our own pinafores, by hand. The teacher would help you and show you - what to do and get on with it. Then when you're finished she used to show the class which one was - was the best out the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents ever visit the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Yes, used - they used to go there. Mother and father used to go there then. Specially when we had concerts, we used to do singing. The whole school - in a group. Used to have concerts
 at the end of - term. We used to have singing and dressing up and - play games and all kinds of things. The mother and fathers - everybody's mother and father could go to to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did other children at school come from similar types of home from your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh no, some of them - not many of them was - homes like our - mine. No, no. 'Cos I said to them, do - do you say your grace when you get up to the table? Oh no. Well, I said, we have to. Why don't you? Oh, it doesn't matter about that do
es it? Well, I said, it does in our family. I said, and if you said it the wrong way round, I said, we used to have to get out and have nothing. So they said, oh well, my mother and father doesn't bother about anything like that. Well, I said, mine 
\endash  mother and father do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So most of them were rougher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Much rougher, yes. The two girls where I - had friends, their - mother and father was similar to mine. 'Cos they used to go - with them - you know, to their Sunday school and see what they done or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember what your friends' father's did for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
One of them was a - worked in a fish shop. And the other one worked in a bakers. And - sometimes we'd bring home a little piece of extra bread or - piece of cake and he'll say, give it to - a piece to your friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In what ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If you could do something better than they could do, used to go out the front - o
f the class and do it. Read it or sing it. In front of the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, there were different groups - you had groups for different - games like. Rounders and - different things and - sing on the w
ay, I forget the song now what we used to sing as we used to go round hopping, on one leg all the way round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about amongst the children the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 selves, playtime or that, were there any gangs there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, in - when we had our playtime we used t
o play - different games, it was mostly cigarette pictures those days, we used to play, or marbles and - used to pick your own friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you remember any children being left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, most - most children - would play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you go on to another school after this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, only that one. And - those - only two schools I went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How old were you when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you have stayed any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I - cos I wanted to - go out and mind - a baby. I wanted to absolutely take children over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, I think I could have - liked to have done if 
- but of course - as the family was poor and - you just couldn't in those days, you had - just had to leave school and - go out and earn some money, and used - those days you see you weren't paid in weekly - wage, you were paid monthly. See, and it used t
o be very poor, perhaps ten shillings the month. And used to give that up at home I used to, and I had a shilling out of that. That was to buy my clothes with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 Do you think you benefi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 ted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Any special ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
I think singing and - knowing how to dress yourself properly, things like that, 'cos - a - a dirty child would be brought out the front, and - and a clean one, and - teacher would say, well what - do you think of this nice clean person? What d
o you think of this girl, what - to yourself. Surely you could have washed yourself before you come to school. Things like that, perhaps they'd just got out of bed and run to school. Without brushing their hair or anything like that. Well my father would 
never let us come to the table without we'd washed and brushed our hair. That was not allowed at our - in our house. But other peoples houses you could just - go in and - filthy dirty hands and go to the table, but we weren't allow - allowed to do that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 While you were at school, you told me that you had several odd jobs for earning money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Are there any you haven't told me about, any other regular jobs you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well I told you about collecting in washing up and down the - carol singi
ng. Doorstep cleaning and brass, and going looking after children. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did you find these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well - this church I went to - and these children were brought there, as babies, with their parents. And they - said to me one day, would you l
ike to come and look after - Tony - and Daphne, that was their two names, so I said, oh I would love to. So they said, well could you come on a Saturday? So I said, yes. I'd love to do that. So they said, well when you leave school, do you think you would
 
like to come with us and live with us, and look after our two children? I said, yes, I would if my mother and father - would let me. So I went home to my mother and father and I said, well when I leave school, I've only got about three weeks to go, can I 
g
o with the Thomsons were their name, I said, could I go with Mr and Mrs Thomson, they're going to go and move to Little Wakering, and they want me to be - a little nanny to their - two children. So she said, yes. And I stayed with them for four years. And
 then I bettered myself. With a higher position, in with the nanny business. And I took over two boys. And I was a real nanny then. And that was at Beckenham, Kent. And I stopped there until I was - twenty-four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you left school, that would be 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Thirteen when I took me job on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you were with these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Four years I was with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That would be 1917, just before the war ended then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You went to Beckenham while the war was still on did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Loved it there. Beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you tell me exactly what you had to do? Could you tell me what hours you worked in this first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well I got up about - seven o'clock in the morning. Then I went into the children you see. 'Cos they was alw
ays awake - and - up by eight o'clock they was dressed, and washed and dressed by me. And - went down to breakfast. Then all I done then was to take them out for all the morning. And come back and have our dinner. Then perhaps - the smallest one would hav
e
 a little sleep. Then I used to look after the other one by - half past two I was out again with them. See, 'cos there was a park near they and they used to love running round the park. Then I used to bring them home again. Then they used to have their te
a and used to give them a - bath. Then put to bed. Then I could do any jobs I wanted to, which I mended their clothes. Children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s clothes. And done their little bits of washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many servants were kept at this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Two. A cook - and a - a general maid. And myself, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did you sleep and eat, the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
I - I had a morning room to meself with the children. Yes. But every now and again I'd like to sneak out you see to the kitchen to learn how to do a little bit of - cooking. I was very fond of cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there a servants hall or anything like that at that place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, there was no servants hall, they had their - food - the other two, in the kitchen. There was just the morning room for the - for the nanny and the two children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You always had your meals with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Always had my meals with the children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the mistress supervise all housework personally or did she pass orders through the other servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, she - the mistress of th
e house - passed the orders - through. Then after a - a little while I think it was about a year and a half - they had a pony and trap. And - so - I could learn how to drive the pony and trap with the two children in it. And I used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You used to go out on your own with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Without - with me own, in - with the children in the pony and trap and that was really lovely. Yes, used to take them about three miles - three and three miles back and - used to be very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was after you moved to Wakelin was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. When we went - moved to Wakelin, 'cos it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long had you been working for them when you moved to Wakelin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh quite a long time when I was a child here about - I should say about nine you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When you started full time work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, full time work. Oh - immediately. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So we are talking about Wakelin?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Wakelin, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you feel at ease with the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they were very kind to me. Used to say to me, now any
thing you want to know just come and tell me, and I'll - mind you I was rather - knowing for me age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about with the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 There was only Mr and Mrs - Williamson, they used to have lots of parties - in the house. Yes. And the
n - those party days - which they entertained quite a lot - perhaps I used to help - out in the kitchen. Perhaps I could carry something for them in the dining room, 'cos they used to give big tips those days, the visitors. And then those days - the serva
nts could go into the morning room with me and have their meal that night. That was the only time. But I used to love helping them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did servants and members of the family address each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh madam and sir and - always. Never Mrs or - Mr. Yes, m'm and no m'm and - yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did they address the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Madam. Well they used to call them by their names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 Their surname or C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 hristian name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Surnames.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you feel that any of them was interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, they were. Yes. Apparently I knew - quite a lot of little bits and pieces in the way of sewing what they wanted to know what to do, 'cos in those days they wore - caps and frilly - they said, do you think you could do that for me? I said, oh yes, 
I - I'll manage to do that for you. They said, well we'll give you something for it. I said, well I don't want it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the master or the mistress, do you think they were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes. They didn't think I would
 learn so quickly. With children, it was so - they didn't know why so I said, well I've been - brought up with children all my life and I've always fetched babies to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the mistress give any moral guidance to her servants at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No
t - not - not very often, she used to leave you - quite alone. Because she used to go out rather a lot. She used to go to town - and leave you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to go out when you liked and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no, no, no, you didn't go out wh
en you liked. You had - you had an afternoon and evening, and you had one whole day a month. That's - that's all what you had, you never went out when you liked. Only - I could go out when I liked with the children, yes. But - if I wanted to go out on my 
own - see I had a certain day to go out on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 On your free evening did she want to know where you were going or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh it was always - I went - I wanted to go home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But did she expect to know where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No
. No, she didn't bother but I used to say I'm going home, and she used to know I wanted to go home. So she used to say, well you can go a little earlier then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you feel homesick when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Just at first I did. Just at first, but - the two - maids there made me - quite at home. So I didn't feel homesick then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you lonely or did you have enough companionship there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I had quite enough companionship. I wasn't lonely at all, 'cos I used to do - I used to knit the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s socks and - always working - making things for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about that situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I don't there think was anything I disliked at all. No. Another thing you see it was a nice big garden a
nd they had chickens at the bottom. And they had - rabbits, they bred rabbits. Had two dogs. And I was fond of - very fond of the garden and - had one of those swinging - chairs you could sit in, you know, with the children when the - maid used to bring u
s - our tea. It was very very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How old were the children when you first went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well, one was two. And the other one was three and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This is when you started full time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did the housework go there, who made or mended the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They had somebody outsider to do that. Yes, somebody they - they'd known for years an old lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the washing, was that sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That was sent out, oh yes, sent out - all the laundryman used to cal
l - once a week, and bring it home in a basket, all nicely done - those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well the general maid - not the cook. She put all the washing away and see to it all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the cook do all the cooking or did the mistress ever do any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, the mistress never done any. No. I used to try and get in there and see if I could have - have a go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What were your duties apart from looking after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Play with the
m. That was me duty to play with the children you see and see if they was - happy and - I've always had children with me. And see they never got into any mischief or - anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You didn't have to do anything else around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no. No. No. Only make the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s beds, had to do that, and my own bed. But not anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How much time did the children spend with their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They always saw their mother and father every night. Regular. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long would that be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well, half an hour. And Sundays - extra, about an hour or so - with their mother and father, perhaps their mother and father would take me as well, with the two children, in a - a car, 'cos they had - both had a car each, and take us out f
or a drive. Perhaps go and see one of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \rquote 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
s - aunties or uncles, see and I was with them. Then when they got too tired you see - and the father, they used to run us home. And - so I could put them to bed and they went back again. Which that was very nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was a regular visiting routine, were there any haphazard times they would see them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no. No. No, they would always want to see the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever see them at bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, at bedtime, when they 
were home, or even - when they were asleep, before ever the mother and father went to bed, they went in to see the - children, give them a goodnight's kiss, always. But then if the mother and father was home they used to say what they had done, the childr
en, during the day, to the mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
and father. Oh you've done that have you, oh that was nice and you enjoyed that. Talked to them like that, very nicely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would they ever be there when they were dressing in the morning or having a bath or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, no, mother and father wasn't there then, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Whereabouts in the house would the child see its parents, would this be in the nursery or the drawing room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, the drawing room more or less. Yes. I used to say to 'em, now you can run down and see mummy and daddy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were the parents away very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, they were rather - away a lot. He was in - well she was a singer. Yes. And the father was a shipping - director. Shipping line, which was - jolly good job. Sometimes he come home a little bit tipsy. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She used to sing professionally did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. And - of course that's why I was left - so much alone with the children you see, she wanted somebody that she could trust and rely on. She knew the children be quite 
all right, and of course the others, the cook and the - nanny was very fond of them, she used to say to me, you're absolutely spoiling them, but I wasn't spoiling them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the children have any tasks to carry out in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no, not
 the children, no. No. No, nothing at all. Except the liked to go down and pick up the eggs. Chickens. Used to love doing that. Had a little basket each.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the older child help the younger one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes, lit - used to help - you put it in 
there. See? Used to help one another. Yes. Oh yes, they were very fond one another, often see them giving themselves a cuddle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What was the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh six o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you always put them to bed or would the mother do it sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, no, I always put them to bed and I used to read them a story or make up a story they used to like a - you know, different kinds of story about a little dickey bird or something like that and he - he'd got into a water can, you know, and 
he couldn't get out. Well how did he get out then? All things like that, they used to love - specially made up stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the children share a bedroom or bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, they had a bed each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the same room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 At what age did they put themselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well I never known 'em - much to put themselves to bed, not until they was about six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Can you remember sleeping arrangements of the whole family there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - the children used to have their ro
om, and I had a door - which was a little room, so if I hear the children I could just go in to them. The mother and father had the largest room downstairs. And the cook had a room to herself and the other one had a - room to herself. Then there was still
 another two - spare bedrooms. A lounge, a morning room, and a big dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have a bathroom there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Nice large bathroom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was for the servants as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 As - as well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How often did the children bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh every day I used to bath them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, ev - I - perhaps twice a day I'd change them. I liked to be particular with them, yes. Twice a day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You didn't worry about the dirty washing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No, no
, nothing like that, they had plenty of clothes, I could change them three times if I wanted to. Especially if they was going out to a friend and I was going with them to have tea with another little - two little children. Yes, oh yes, change them again, 
make them look nice. Oh the mother was very proud because I could do that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did the children eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the - in the morning room with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was always was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Except Sundays. Then they'd go in with mummy and daddy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would that be for every meal on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If the mother and father was there, if they weren't out - asked out. Yes. The only two children they - ever had you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did the adults eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did the parents eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they - always in the dining room. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of cooking equipment was there in the house, was it gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Gas. Gas cooking, yes. Plenty of good cooking too. Store cupboard was - oh - stacked, there wasn't one tin of fruit, there - mig
ht have been fifty tins of different kinds of fruit. Yes. And you was never stinted for food. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there any homemade bread or bottled fruit, things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, oh yes, yes, homemade bread as well. Yes. Bottled fruit. Bottled - tomato
es. All different kinds of things bottled. Jam making, marmalade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Pickles - chutney. All kinds of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the cook do all this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No, the - the - other maid would help her. Yes, she would help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the mistress do anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, no, she never done it, no. I used to sneak out sometimes and say can I come out, and they said yes. The - lady won't be home tonight so you're all right. You can come and have a go. 'Course and I learnt a lot by that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any wines or beers made there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - wine cellar. Mm. Wine cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I suppose you found this quite a change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Wine cellar. Yes. Now sometimes - Mr Williams used to say to me now I'm going to let you do this tonight. Now you have the wi
ne - cellar key, and you get me up - perhaps champagne - or port, sherry, bottle of whisky, and a bottle of gin. Now, he said, you go and do - find that all for yourself and you bring it all up. He said, that's - see then you've got to lock the - that up.
 
Then those occasion when there was a large party he used to bring up a bottle of - sherry - for the - cook, housekeeper, and he said only just a little for you. That used to be lovely. And if you went home, he knew you went home - not every time, used to 
say, you can take that home - a bottle of that to your mother and father, I never said anything that me mother and father never drunk because mother and father gave it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you yourself didn't object to drink on principle then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well not - not
 then, not those days, not when I was doing it, only just a little with - the others. I liked to be friendly with the others. But my father wouldn't have drink in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When was breakfast eaten there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Eight o'clock as a rule. Nine o'clock for the children and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So the parents would eat first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of food did you have breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, cereals, porridge. Bacon and egg. Eggs, scrambled egg. Omelettes. Toast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there anything different on Sundays or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, used to - sausages - perhaps sausages with the - bacon and eggs. Mushrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What about other meals, how about the midday meal, what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh we always had a nice cooked day - midday meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would the parents be at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, they - no, no, no, they wouldn't be home, not midday meal, only on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you'd have a cooked midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would this be a three course meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - two. Lamb or - greens, carrots, always carrots. 
Potatoes, peas, always a pudding. Steamed pudding, milk pudding. Children used to be very fond of a nice steamed pudding with treacle on. Put the treacle on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What time would you have this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 One o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would the next meal be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That would be teatime at half past - five as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Bread and butter and - cakes and - perhaps jelly. Or fruit in jelly, cream.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the parents, when would they have their main meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Main meal, if they were in always used to be at half past seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This would be a full cooked meal would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Full cooked meal, yes. With soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were the fruit and vegetables grown there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Grown - yes, down at the bottom of the garden, we had a gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have any other outdoor servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, just this gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he live in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, he didn't live in, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were any vegetables and fruit and things bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Very seldom. Very seldom. It was a very large patchy a
t the bottom of the garden. 'Cos fruit trees, plum trees - gooseberry bushes, blackcurrants, red currants, all kinds like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they keep any livestock, I know you said - you kept hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, chickens and rabbits. And - dog - these two dogs and - and a bird.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there any tinned meat used then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Occasionally, not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many times a week was meat eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the children and servants and parents all have the same food or different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, always the same food. Nothing different between the servants. They had exactly the same as the others. If there was a mixed grill with steak, kidney, liver, bacon - they had exactly the same as the others.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were the children allowed to talk at meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Sometimes I'd let them talk but very seldom they did. They used to - like their food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No they had - piece of everything, they never - was brought up to - not to like this and not to like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What was said if something was left uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, well I said you can't have any tea. If you leave that you can't eat tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you used to stick to your word?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
I stuck to me word, yes. Yes. And that usually used to go down. And they - I should - help them with it of course. I'd say now then, that's quite all right, now you can have your tea. I said, now we'll have a 
nice little - little five minutes rest, I said, then we'll go out and we'll have nice little game. They used to love that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If there was something on the table out of reach like the salt or anything like this, could they ask someone to pass it or did t
hey have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, they'd ask, could they have the salt or anything like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, oh yes, if they wanted a second helping they could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could toys or books be brought to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, no, no, no. They were never brought - in to the table, no, no. Left in the nursery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When could they leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When I told them to. When they said their grace. I taught them to say - say their grace. 
When they get up to the table, nicely you know - now the leg's not quite nicely under the table. Now sit nice - straight and upright, now say your grade, and they used to say their grace. And say their grace when they got down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about holding their knife and fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they were quite good with that, very very good indeed. Yes. Real respectable children. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was the mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes, she was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say she was an affectionate mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Yes, she was nice. Directly she came in - she'd say - how have they been today? What have you done, and all this kind of thing. She'd know all about them, what have they done, what have they said, all kinds of things. Perhaps I'd do a l
ittle drawing and - hold their hand so they could - show mummy when she come in, and daddy what they'd done. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was the father the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, oh yes, rather, he loved the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think the children felt they could share their worries with their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, they - and with me, yes, put their arms around me, never let me go sometimes. And I used to say, now you must go to mummy. No. No, I don't want to, I want to be with you. I - I
 said, well - now do go and see mummy, mummy does love you. No, I - I want to be with you. 'Course I - I'm passionately fond of children to this day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did the parents expect the children to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they - absolutely re - respe
cted their mother and father. It was hear - directly they heard their mummy and daddy come in the door - that's if they were awake - or on a Sunday, perhaps I'd say now - run down and you can go in to mummy's bed - in - get in the bed with mummy and daddy
. Just for a little while. Then come up again quickly, and they did. Mm. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you tell the children how to behave towards their brothers and their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, I used to say - say - teach all that, oh yes. Say now you shouldn't have done that now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If the child was hit by another child would you tell them to hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh no. No, I wouldn't do that. No. No. I would just say now - if the child wants hitting it will be smacked by me, not by you. You must never - touch these children. But that very - that - never happened though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did the children behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh - passionately fond of me. Yes. Absolutely. They'd come and run into my bed - in the morning directly I woke up and put their arms round me and then they wanted a story straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When grown ups were talking were the children allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not - not as a rule, no. No, they were very quiet. I even took them to a hotel for a month on my own. Yes. And they were marvellous. And 
the mother came down and father at the weekend to see how we were getting on. And they didn't want to go back with the mother and father. No. They said, do you want to come back with us tonight? No. No. No. No, we want - we want to stay, we're going to ha
v
e a nice - bathe, and play sands in the morning and we - of course I used to do it all with them you see. But they were very very good with the water. Always wanted to go down and get in the water. I used to let them. 'Cos I used to undress myself and of 
course. Lovely. Yes, and - and usually I had another nanny come with me, and she'd got three boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were these friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Friends of the - Williams. Then it was their hotel we stayed in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 At Ramsgate. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What kind of people did the parents hope the child would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well one wanted to be a sailor. That's 'cos his daddy was to do with the ships you see. Going out to sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think the parents considered certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I don't know, I don't think so. They left it to - to you to see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you teach them that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I used to say, you know, when you - when you're growing up, you know, like dadd
y and - you've got to - do different things, you can't do like you do today, you've got to be a big man and help - help other people and - help poor people and old ladies and gentlemen, all things like that. 'Cos they used to say to me, what's that - lady
 got a stick for, what's that man got a stick for? Why is that man being wheeled about? And I used to say all that to them you see, I said, oh well - when you're a big man you'll be able to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think your attitude was similar to their parents on these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did they parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - oh no, never heard - anything like that, no, no, never, nothing - nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If the child did something the parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well they just used to have to go without something. They used to be very fond of - rainbow, these - comic books. See, well they - couldn't have that, and that was meant. If they'd done something very wrong - and I said they had, they had
 to go without their comic. And that done more to them than anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were they ever punished physically? Did they ever get a slap or a cane or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, only a slap. Must - never never - never - never caning, oh no, no, no, no, no. I co
uld just smack them for not - for doing that at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the parents used to punish them then for serious things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not really, no. No, the parents never touched it, if I - they said you sort of smacked them they said, we leave that to you. 
They said, we - they don't want two people doing the things, they only want one. Which is quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
How did you feel about the way the parents wanted to bring up their child? Did you ever feel on the side of the child more than the parents sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I liked the child better than the parents, definitely. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But did you ever disapproved of the parents attitude to children in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Sometimes, if they was - you know, a little bit too - wanted 'em to do this too much, I 
felt as though - I didn't approve of it very much. I suppose it's because I had more to do with them I didn't want 'em to interfere with 'em - so much. 'Cos they were really very clever children. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s birthdays any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, they really had a party. Yes, they had quite - I should say ten children in. Quite ten children. And that was usually out in the garden we had that party. Then I used to hide - little treasures out in the garden for them to find
, wrap things up you see for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would they have presents, what sort of presents did they have, did they have a lot of presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - lot of presents, and elaborate presents, yes. And so did we at Christmas time from them. Yes. Yes, yo
u always had a five pound note. Yes. Beside other little things given to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How much were your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was paid monthly. It was two pound ten a month. That was quite a good wage in those days. And of course I went up from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Can you remember anything that the family did together on Christmas Day, now how would the family spend their Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, elaborate. Have friends in and - everybody would join in. The nursery would be - decorated up. The morning room, the drawing room, a
ll be decorated up. And everybody would have their presents after breakfast. Used to be a big Christmas tree. Of course the children used to come down and - everybody used to - servants as well. After breakfast everybody went into the room and had their p
resents. And there used to be a big party in the evening. The children used to have a little party in the - afternoon. With one or two friends what used to come in. They had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would the parents go to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh the parents - all the parents, yes, w
ould be in with that. Have games, hide things under chairs and all kinds of things we used to do for them. Then - we had a piano of course there was - the little ones used to - sing, one of them - we used to put one in the corner, she always wanted to go 
in the corner, and - and - and sing. I forget, what did she sing now? Mark - held a candle and that she used to hold.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The other servants wouldn't be there during this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, they would be - after that, yes. Oh they used to be elaborate time there at Christmas. Plenty to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever make music together as a family other times at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they used to play the piano and sing, they used to have - friends in at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any other instruments besides the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, just the piano, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the parents play games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, they'd play games with the children, yes. Father used to like playing games and hiding things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, different kinds of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to read them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, if you wanted to - read a book you could - have a book, yes, plenty of books in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh always plenty of newspapers and magazines, always. And when t
hey've finished with the magazines you could have them if you wanted to - take them home when you went you could take them home with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember the mother or father reading aloud to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, reading aloud, sitting on the bed, reading aloud to them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember attending a funeral in the family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I've never - no, no funeral there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You had full dealings with the children, you'd take them out walking? Did you used to go out shopping at all with them, things like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes. Yes. If they wanted new - new clothes and things like that perhaps the mother used to come then, we used to go up in the West End, very nice, we had our lunch up there as well. Lovely time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to talk to people while you were out with the children on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Only with other nannies. I was with other nannies, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever take the mistress's child to your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You told me about going away for a month on holiday, could you tell me about any other holidays or Bank Holidays you went on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What, when I was with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you used to go away with the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Went to Paignton - with the mother and father and the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you usually had a long summer holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Month. And all together. We used to go down to the - we had a - a tent, see, where we could change, and - they used to have an
other friend - husband and wife used to go with us, and of course they were fond of the children, so - we all went in the water together, all of us. Very nice too. Nice hotel we stayed at. And I had a room in with the children then. Not a room to meself. 
In with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You really used to like these holidays did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - lovely. Absolutely. Yes, because they used to take us different places you see, we all went together. 'Cos we had two cars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they seem any different on holiday than when they were a home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, they used to say, if you went - here's - that's a half a crown, go and get yourself something now, I'll just look after the two children, don't worry about the children, just you go - for a half an hour - on your own and find yourself something.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So they'd give you a bit of free time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you felt it was a holiday did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Absolutely. Yes. It was always about three times a week they'd say, there you are look, there'
s some money there, now you just go for a little way on your own. Don't worry about the children, they'll be all right. Well look after them. I thought to myself, well perhaps they just want them for a half an hour or an hour on their own and they want to
 
try and get rid of me if I can. Because the children would keep following me, they wouldn't follow their mother and father you see. And I used to say to 'em, now don't - now go with mummy now, go along. They'd say, no, we want to go with you, we want to h
ave a - 'cos I used to have a good old game with them you see in the water, that's what they loved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the master and mistress think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I don't think so, I - they liked me to go - to be a little bit on the 
religious side with the children. I - used to say it was Sunday to the children. And I used to say, we shall sing one or two little - hymns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you take them to church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 A little church, yes, in a Sunday school. And they used to like - Je
sus - meek and gentle. And all Things Bright and Beautiful. I used to love to hear them sing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the parents go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they went. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you used to go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No, no, no, I never went with the parents, never o
nce. If their friends rung up and said they're going to church they said well we'll meet you and off they used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did any of the servants attend the same church as the master and mistress?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was a different church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there ever family prayers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Family prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Just the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The parents, yes. Oh yes, I used to like the prayers. The children used to kneel down at the side of the bed
. Yes, and they used to say - at Christmas time, do you think Je - Jesus has heard us? And if' I'm naughty tonight - Jesus won't bring me anything will he? I said, no, he won't, I said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 At this place did the master and mistress take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know what their views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Conservative they were. They were Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they play a very active part or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they used to - decorate the car. And - go round the streets - calling out. And collecti
ng people at night time, specially those elderly people who couldn't go but - the car - not like today, you know, just the little bit of - it was real decorated. Real Conservative. Ribbons and - across the bonnet and the lot. Made a - quite - quite a do o
f it. It was very nice. And she did too. Took a great interest in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the master take part in any sport, did he go to the races or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not the races, no, he used to like golf. Golf and cricket. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he go to a club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, he went to a club - with friends what he'd go down there. This - golf - wasn't very far away this golf course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they used to play cards, used to play whist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the mistress, did she have interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, she had - interests in - outside the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She used to go round visiting people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did she work for charities and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 For charities, she used to like - blind and
 Doctor Barnardo's Home. Matter of fact, we had - one - time - near Christmas time, a lot of - Doctor Barnardo's children in the house, and - they done a little play, and some singing. Then they wrote out a cheque for them. And we gave them some food, the
 children, and it was very enjoyable evening, lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did she sit on committees and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, she did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did she go out on her own very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, she went out her own a lot. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did she go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We
ll, she used to go up to town. Practically every day she used to go to the West - to town, yes. She was a very smart woman and - as I said, she went out singing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they go out together very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, yes, used to go out together, frie
nds, dinners, big dinners. Masonic does. Round Table they had and - different things like that. Specially for children they done quite a lot for children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think I asked you the master's occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 A - a ship. In the shipping - direct - director, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did this ever take him away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Occasionally, yes. He stopped away, perhaps - a fortnight or three weeks at a time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know where he used to have to go or why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I don't really know why he went away those 
- those times. When he did come home I knew he'd got plenty of wine and everything with him and he used to come in just - just rolled in the door and drop on the floor. And there used to be the cook and the maid used to pick him up and put him on the sett
ee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He really used to go out did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, it really used to drop right out, and once - his wife - we had a - the railway station running at the bottom, rail - rail line, and - his wife was over the other side - to - of the friend which was ill an
d - she rung up, wanted to know if he was home, of course - we'd put him on the settee you see and he was, you know, right out, and - the phone went and - Mrs Williams wanted him, to speak to him you see and you'd got to go up the stairs to get to the tel
ephone. And - well - we helped to push him up the stairs you see, and - he got hold of the telephone you see to speak to her and he wrenched it right - right off the wall and fell down on the floor again, and that was the end of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of these goings on after being in a teetotal household at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well I don't think much of it at all really. Although I - when I was older I - you know, me - I got - I thought to myself, well I'd better get used to this kind of thing, this is what 
happens when you get older. Apparently this is what - goes on. Especially in his line, see, I mean he had - tasted - had to taste all this wine and different stuff. See, and then the - sometimes he'd tasted a little too much and - with his friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this shipping company connected with wine then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, all wine, every kind of wine you could think of. You see. And it used to come in crates - to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He was a wine shippers was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. And all this wine used to come, we used to put it down the cellar. I thought I was it when I had the key of the wine cellar that day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did this alter your opinion of the upper class or the rich at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, I thought why should they have all this and - the poor people can't get anythin
g at all. To me all that was a lot of waste of money, going down the sink. Whereas poor people, they could have - done with a - a loaf of bread or a - or - some meat, something like that, clothes. I used to think that was terrible. Blind drunk and couldn'
t stand on your feet when another poor soul could have done with a jolly good dinner. That was in my - I grew out of it when I got - up to thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did it make any difference to the way the household was run when the master was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not really, n
o, no, only you - he never took a lot of part in the - as long as he saw everything done and he paid up and - the gardener was doing his job which he did, he kept the garden beautiful. And of course - the cars were beautifully kept. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was the mistress ever away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - I think she was only away about twice all the time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this for long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, through illness. That's why she went. And that was about one or two nights. And they - they died, but we - I - I d
idn't see the funeral 'cos it wasn't at our - our house at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So normally she was always at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Always at home, yes. 'Cos they were people what entertained a lot. They used to like entertaining more than they went out. To their friends you see. Of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you describe these occasions for me? Were they dinner parties mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, well a real dinner party, a - you know, a good roast. A turkey or goose or - aitch bone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many people would they have round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well someti
mes used to be twenty. Then you used to get - a big tip then, and that used to be shared out with me as well. Because I used to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would they do after dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, sing and - play cards and - dominoes and - what's that other - game, whi - which Bridge. Played bridge. They played bridge a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever have dancing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, they had a dance, yes, 'cos - they had parquet flooring - where the piano was and they had dancing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What kind of people were these friends they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, very rich people. Yes. Got plenty of money. Slip a pound note in your hand. They'd say - have - that's for you. Yes. Very rich people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know what their occupations were any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 One of them was in the shipping line with Mr Williams. Yes. I don't know what the others were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mainly business friends do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Business friends. Oh, and another one had got a - his own business, like a pub. That's up in the West End. Large place. And a hotel - 
with it. That's the Nolands, and that's the nanny I went with with her - three boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They were the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Class of - as - the Williams, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What class would you say that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, they was very very nice, lovely people. Lovely people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was the mistress from the same class as the master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Did the master and mistress treat some of their friends differently from others, would they put on more of a show for some than others or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I never n
oticed anything different at all like that. They liked - when they - done a thing they done it real proper. They had the lot. Done the same for everyone, yes. And of course we used to enjoy it you see 'cos we used to hear the singing and - they all used t
o join in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say most of the guests used to tip you very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did they treat you in other ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Respected us, very much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did some of the guests treat you differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Some would give you more than others, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think your master and mistress were content with their station in life or do you think they would have liked a higher position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I think they were quite satisfied as they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They struck you as being -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Just what they wanted. Just right. They were quite happy together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Had you known people like your master and mistress before you went into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of them and their way of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well, of course 
it was quite different to what I'd been used to. See I mean I - never seen - bottles of wine on the table in me life. Nor three glasses, you know, on the table or laid out like that I - couldn't make out what it was all for. I soon found out though. Didn'
t take me long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did their manners and general behaviour seem different from the people you'd known before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they were very very - nice people. Their manners were beautiful. They never just pass you by or anything like that, they'd ask you how y
ou are, anything like that. If you're not feeling well you shouldn't be up, and you must go back to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You moved from there then about 1917 or 18?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did you go from there, you went to another family, was this still as a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Still as a nanny. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Why did you leave these people, you seemed quite happy there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Well - because I thought I'd better have a better position, and more money I wanted. That is why. And that was advertised and I thought to myself that sound
ed very very nice. And I could have a car to meself or - with a chauffeur, to take the children out. And I was getting twice the amount of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How much were you earning by the time you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 About - just on three pound a month, which wasn't m
uch. And this one's going to be nearly twice the amount of money. And I was going to have clothes, which they was going to buy for me. Yes. So I thought - I'd better take - this - move, to a better position, which I did. And I've never regretted it. I've 
showed you the photographs of meself didn't I with the child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did your master and mistress think of this when you wanted to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they didn't like it at first. But unfortunately - I hadn't been left - there six months - when Mrs Willia
ms died. So - I thought to myself - well it was very sad at me leaving there but in a way I was glad, because - I knew - that he would remarry again very soon. Because I could tell that - when they had these parties, you can always tell - that - if anybod
y was - fond of somebody, which he was fond of one person there -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He had his eye on somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Eye had - he had his eye on someone, yes, and - she died of over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13132348\charrsid479496 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 drinking, whisky. So the boys were put to boarding school, the girl and the boy. So in 
a way I was very pleased I took the decision, I didn't want to leave the children, I wanted them to come with me but I knew like - I'd got to hurry up and break away from them, which I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So presumably if she died six months later she was pretty bad while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. It was drink what done it. See she had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This must have been quite a shock to you, all these goings on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was a shock to me. Yes. It was real - a shock. To think - a - a nice person like her, which was - had a 
good voice - but of course, she would never - take a cup of tea in the morning, if you know what I mean, she would take a glass of whisky. See, well that's no good to a woman is it. I mean that's going to ruin you - in the end, well that was what done it 
for her. See, and her two boys had to be put away to a boarding school. Which was a terrible shame.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you were quite conscious of the master having his eye on someone else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. And I was quite right. He married her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was that much of that sort of going on in that class of society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. I - I - I tumbled to it after I'd been there a year. 'Cos he - you know, had his eye on me once or twice, and I - was a bit cute about it. I thought myself, hm - you're not playing any monkey tricks with me. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You were very young for him to try anything like that weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, but - any rate - he said - he - once he got - he said, oh I could just squeeze you, you're such a little dear. So - I didn't like that. And - that went on - t
wo or three times like that. And I didn't want anything to happen to me. But - he could see, I said to him, I don't want any monkey tricks. I just told him about it. Especially as I found out he - well I caught him once you see, with - this women and - he
 knew I did and he told me - he said, I - here you are, I'll give you something, but don't say anything. Of course I wouldn't say anything. He said, you put that in your pocket, don't say anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That was one of the times the mistress was away was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Surely they must know the servants are liable to catch them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. Catch them at any time you see. Well I - I - well the others didn't have much - to do with them, perhaps I - I think I - one of the - children wasn't well. And I just
 happened to - say - to him - that I think I'd better ring - for the doctor you see and I just - happened to go in at the wrong time. And - I knew that's really what he wanted to - try this tricks with me. And I - I wasn't having any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Coming form your background this must have been quite an eye opener?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
It came - it - it - it was an eye-opener for me. I thought to myself does this go on for always? Every place I go to. Is this going to happen everywhere I go. But of course it didn't you se
e. When I went to the other place, it was a different place altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They were much more respectable were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They - well there wasn't the drink and things there you see. To start with. Much more respectable people. They were church people 
you see. Well matter of fact he was a minister. Of a church. And I had much higher wages and I was really respected and he respected me, both of them did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 As a child you told me for example the incident when you went into a rich house up on Muswell Hill when you were Christmas carolling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Obviously as a girl you looked up to or respected the rich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I did respect the rich, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did this like affect your view of the rich when you actually saw how they behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes
, yes, it did, 'cos I thought to myself, well this is if what the rich do - well I don't think much about it. I'd sooner a poorer person than that. Apparently this was - the rich do then to people. If they fancy anybody, apart from their wife, I thought m
yself, well I wasn't - I don't care for that. Of course I don't care for it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This other place you went you say he was a minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He was a minister, yes. Well I wasn't christened. So I - went to his church in the morning, and he christened me
, at that age. You see, it was very very nice indeed, 'cos they brought me my dress and everything. Had a nice cream dress on, and it got little - cherries hanging down, and I had a nice veil and - beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were the rest of your brothers and sisters christened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Why was this, because your parents were quite interested in religion and church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they thought perhaps we'd make up our own minds afterwards. Yes. Which everybody has been christened. Since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say this was your father's idea or your mother's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Me father's idea. But the very last - baby, they did go - have - him christened, mother and father went together at the church, but none of the others. Of course this was a very church - going - place I was a
t you see. And the first thing he asked me you see, I wanted to be confirmed. And he said to me have I been christened, and I said no. So he said well of course you'll have to be christened before you can be confirmed. So I said, oh - when - when will tha
t happen? So he said, well we'll do it one morning, Sunday morning, in church, he said, you'll like that. He said, now don't worry about anything, he said, we'll buy the things for you. And you'll be quite all right, and I was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long did you stay with this household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I stayed there for six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That would be about to 1920?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Mm. I went away - as I thought I'd better have another - they wrote for me to go back again - to them, which I did. I went back, and - stayed another two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Have you always been a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you work after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You carried on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I carried on looking after children. And - matter of fact I've done lot of - nursing with elderly people as well. Sometimes I get call
ed out now. If anybody's - very ill, could I run round and - just - see if they want the hospital or if anything I can do for them. Often I have a - ring at the bell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you take up nursing after you stopped being a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 About when was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That - that was about when I was about twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So that would be about 1925 you stopped being a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mm. Yes, I wanted to be - a nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You took up nursing, was this private nursing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Private nursing I wanted to do. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, more or less full time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long did you carry on with that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Up until - 1950, then I - my back - I had trouble with my - back, and that had to be put in a plaster case. And the doctor sai
d I'm afraid you'll have to give up. He said, you won't be able to lift, which I couldn't you see. But I have - been at places since then, and slept there. And - looked after 'em, in a - room by the side, until they've died. And I've - earnt a good bit of
 money - with that. Old men of eighty and - women of - of eighty. Sent for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No I would not, no, I just wanted nursing and children. I wanted two children of me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Never any training at all. No. I - what I learnt - more - specially when I was in hospital a lot myself, I learnt a lot. And when I was over at Clare Hall - when they had several cases come i
n, I had pneumonia then - several cases came in, very very bad, they got me out of bed and asked me to dress and would I help them. I - helped them with the patients.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No. No, I never belonged to any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers? Some people say that in those days there was a division between trained craftsmen and other workers. Did you feel this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I don't think I did,
 no. If I wanted to know anything special about anything I'd always go to the - sister, and ask. And another thing you see, I've been - convalescent - at All Saints - Eastbourne, and I was there three weeks and I learnt a lot from those convents. I could 
ask them any little thing you see, I said, well I - and I always used to go into their services and prayer, they used to say, we must wait for that little Billy to start us off, with our singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I don't think so, I like - I'm very fond of work. I like work today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We asked you about the details of your occupations up until 1918. You changed jobs just about twelve months before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there much difference in the actual routine of the household?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, quite a lot. Mm, they never had the pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8260480\charrsid479496 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 ties you see for one thing. See they were church - very - church going and they had - church people in there, and had discussions - groups, talking. 
Young people as well, used to have in there. Used to have discussions on different - subjects. No, it's quite a different class altogether, and better class really. I mean the other class was good but it was like - too much drink for my liking. And this -
 was no drink. I never saw any drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were these as rich as the first ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Just as - just as rich I should say. 'Cos they'd got a nice house and a nice garden, and they had a gardener. But it was very very nice in a different way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about your hours of work and this sort of thing, was that much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Just - about the same, I had a - day off a week there and a - day a month. I had. Which I always went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I went to ask you about hour home life after you left school up until
 1918. You weren't living at home but you used to go home on your days off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Home occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. They thought a lot more of me you see. Because I never we
nt home unless I gave them - some money. And sometimes you see I got a parcel of food I could give them. Especially when I was at the place - where they had all this wine and - plenty of - tinned fruit and all that, you see, all the provisions used to com
e in, perhaps they used to say well take - two or three tins of food home with you. And they was very - much different towards me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did this affect your relationship with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well of course they were out working as well.
 And - well we all done the same, we thought - more of one another, we was helping to build the family up you see, it was - mother was - different person altogether. I mean she could have something new for herself which she never had before. See, we thoug
ht well we'll build mother's wardrobe up, let - buy something for her. Not so much me father, but me mother. I thought meself, no, my mother'd help me, I must help her now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, did you still go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When I was with these people? Yes. We had to go - morning and evening. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And at the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you take an interest in politics at this time in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not really, I - I heard a lot about it but I said - I'm not
 quite sure about politics, I think you want to know more about them yourself - before you - take - the decision, although I said I knew I was going to be a Conservative, and I still am a Conservative, and I wouldn't change for anything. My father always 
said be a Conservative and I've followed in his footsteps and I shall never change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You think it's your father's influence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think - my father knows more about the country and the - he really did - study politics. Because he used to be on the do
or, at the polling station, I can remember that quite well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you continue to spend your spare time the same way or did you do different things now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8260480\charrsid479496 - make things for people and se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 ll them. Yes. 'Cos I was always handy with
 me work, and somebody would say to me, could you make me this and - I'd say, yes, well - right up to the - today - I can make a little bit of money for meself. I've made nearly four hundred of those bags - the first one - I made I put in an exhibition an
d made a hat to match, and they came first. And since then I've had - people wanting five, they've gone to Scotland, they've gone - all over the country. Five and six at a time. I've always - I've always come first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This time before 1918 did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, I met new friends. And had a boyfriend. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever take these friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He was my chauffeur. Yes, I took him home, yes, I took him home. Yes, the second place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about at the first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, I had a boyfriend there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where would you go in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh just go to his house. Mm. Which was near there you see, never used to - he lived locally and I couldn't come to London you see just for - evening time. I used to go to his place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you bring him home or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Once. Yes. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where would you go with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well just - more or less walk. Wasn't anywhere else to go really than walk. Those days there wasn't - there wasn't pictures like t
here were today. I know we did go to the pictures once or - went to a concert. I didn't care for that, was too rough for my liking, the concert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where was this, was this the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of concert was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It - was - I don't like any swearing going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was more like a music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, music hall affair, mm. I didn't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where was that, in Wakerin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, in Wakerin. I - I'm no good - I'm no good on the wireless, if - if I hear any - words 
on the wireless, 'cos I think it's unnecessary, I mean surely you can speak without swearing. I can. I can go on for a week without - without swearing. Haven't said anything yet have we. Not going to either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did your parents expect to know your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the parents play any games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, played games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of things did they play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well hunt the thimble and all kinds of things like that. Hiding little parcels in corners and - places like that, yes, use
d to love playing games with the children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you used to play with them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, I loved that, yes, I should say so. Oh I liked anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, plenty of books. You know, religious books, lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8260480\charrsid479496 
s of religious books, encyclopae}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 dias and all those kind of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they have any regular newspaper delivered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, they always had a newspaper delivered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you remember which one it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I believe it was the Mail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I don't remember magazines. Children used to have a Rainbow it was called those days, a comic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the mother or father ever read to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. The children used to take their comics you see and they wan
ted little bits and pieces read out you see and mother and father used to read them out to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there a funeral in the family while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no. No, no, I never seen a funeral there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you used to take the children out walks and shopping didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Not much shopping. Not on me own with them, no. No. That - that wasn't my job to shop. Just occasionally, if - the cook - had run out of anything that was very seldom, then I used to get it, but that wasn't my - part of
 the job at all. That was just a favour to her. That's all. And I never refused 'cos - never. But you never - let on about anything like that you see, you kept it - all that a secret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You were in rather a delicate position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. That's right.
 Yes, you mustn't do anything like that you see, that was not your department to do that kind of thing. But I didn't mind.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were you allowed to talk to people while you were out with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, yes, I could speak to anybody I wanted t
o, with the children, and the - I let the children speak to their different friends, certainly. Those days you see they had those little tiny little - scooter things, well ours hadn't got one but I used to let them go on the others, yes, they loved that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You didn't live near enough to your home to take the children home while you were out
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh no, no, no, no, never took the children home. My parents never saw the children. No. Too far away. And I wasn't anxious to run home in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever go with this master and mistress when they went away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Torquay. Cromer. And Paignton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you go with them if they went to stay with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. Only to a hotel, where we had our own - rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What happened if they went to stay with friends, would they take the children ever, or would they leave the children with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, they'd leave the children behind. To stay with friends, yes, leave the children behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would they do this very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not all that often, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long would it be for as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - never any more than two weeks. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about when you went on holiday with them, how long would this be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well it might be a month. Or it might be three weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So he was a fairly wealthy man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, 'cos - he had - some money left in a will by his side. That's why he - had had this - large house tell you the truth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He wasn't relying on his position in the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No. 
Although money - at the church those days was better than it was today. More people - churches today are half empty. It's terrible really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of activities would you have on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Swimming. Especially the children going in - bathing ev
ery day. And - go for car ride. In the afternoons. Back to the hotel. Of course the children were tired time they'd been out all the morning and perhaps have had a car ride in the afternoon, go back to the hotel and they used to have a bath and I used to 
put them to bed. Then perhaps I used to go out then on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you'd get some free time on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So it was a real holiday for you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Real holiday, yes, although it was a bit hard work with the children, you've got
 to see to the children all the time. They were - I'd got to undress and dress them, especially if they wanted to go - in twice to have a swim, see, 'cos I went in with them. Perhaps our lunch, we'd take our lunch out, midday, perhaps we're never back - w
ent back to the hotel again 'til the afternoon. And that's a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So on the whole you think perhaps you'd work harder on a holiday than when you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well it's rather hard work any rate. 'Cos with children they want you to make thi
s and make the other and build this up for them. But I used to like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you look forward to the holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was a break for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. I used to like to see the sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the master and mistress, did they seem any more friendly or relaxed on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they were very relaxed, yes, and very friendly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 More so on a holiday than at home or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think they were more friendly and - on holiday. Perhaps we'd all go in the sea together you see, and the
n perhaps we'd go out for a trip on the boat. And that used to be rather nice. I used to love that, so did the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What about their attitudes to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 abbath, did they think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh you mustn't do anything l
ike that. Oh no. They don't like that. No, there was very quietness on Sunday. Of course the children used to love to go to the Sunday school and I used to like to go with them. And that was all day like that. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was Church of England was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Church of England. And they - took it in turns with the cook and the maid which they went. To church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they go to the same church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The same church, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did the servants and master and mistress sit, the master would take the service I presume?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh we used to have the pews in the front - of the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You sat with the mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - every time. You never had anything unless we said grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they say family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The servants as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 As well, yes. We had the whole - household. Yes. On the Sunday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was always Sunday was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Always. Regular on a Sunday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you know if the master and mistress took any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, yes, they was quite interested in that, they was Conservative people. Yes. But never used to speak a lot in front of us about anything like that you see. I used to hear them when they'd got friends - ta
lking about politics quite a lot. Liberals some of them were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Some of the friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did I ask you about the Williams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They were, very Con - rank Conservatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You told me about them taking their car out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, rank Conservatives. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the master, did he take part in any sport or go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Golf. No, no, not races. Golf. We had a golf course - wasn't very far away. From us. And we used to - I used to take the children up there as well, because t
here was some seats up there and go and watch. They used to like that, to watch daddy have a game with - his friends, oh and I used to like it of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did he belong to any clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Tennis. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She liked tennis yes, and golf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So they'd go together would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the mistress go out on her own at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did she have her own interests, her own circle of activities?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, she used to go out on her own and have her own - friends of - different meetings. Fellowship }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
s Fellowship. Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s Work meetings. Yes, she was all in that. Sewing - classes and that she'd run. Meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would she be on the committees of charities and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, she was on - lots of charity - committees, yes, she was very interested in things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You've already told me that your master was Holy Orders, was he ever away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, at times. At times. But not for long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long would this before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh it might be for about - three months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where would he go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, if - if - if they wanted a change over for a little while, a minister, then this other minister would take his place, and give - for about thee months. He used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 He would go to some other parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Some other - parish you see. And - then he'd come back to his own - church you see. Oh - several occasions he was away for a time, I mean perhaps he might be called - to take a guild business, in - in an evening - session.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the mistress, did she ever have any business that took her away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She never went - went away from home, not the missus, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You tell us they were quite sociable people, they often had friends and re
latives staying, would they have dinner parties or balls or what sort of affairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they'd have a dance. We had parquet flooring. Yes, they'd have a - nice dance they'd have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What kind of people were their friends and callers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - very very nice people, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were they the same class as the master and mistress?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they were church people, all of them were church people, all - all church people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What class would you say the Thomsons were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well to me, they - I thought they were very - first class. That's to me. They lived up to their religion. And they helped people too. Mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say their friends were the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say they had any friends of a higher class or lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, I - I don't - I think they were just - about - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they treat all their friends the same, would they say give more elaborate entertainment to some than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they'd got one or two different friends of - naturally. Special friends you see, like might lash out a bit more on them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would this be because they were special friends or because they were higher class do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, they - just their special friends I think, not because they were any higher, they liked better you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the behaviour of guests to servants in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh they were very good. They usually tipped servants those days, quite well. Yes. Matter of fact the - cook and the - maid always used to laugh if there was going to be a party because they used to know they're going to get a good tip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How do you think domestic service compared in those days regarding wages and conditions with other employment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well of course those days you see it was very poor
 pay. Today you see you can go and - do a day's - work, and you can get - a pound nearly for the day. In those days you see you get the pound for the month. Quite different pay - those days to what it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In your case it's fairly clear, you like
d children and this sort of thing, but a general maid, why would they prefer to go into service to a factory or something like this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they always had their good food, and a jolly good bed. And perhaps they could take one or two things home with 
them you see, vegetables and things from the garden. They liked it much better than going into a - shop or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So these sort of advantages made up for the low wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I think so, yes. I mean if you consider your food, that's quite a good item is
n't it? Out of a - your wage, all day from morning to night, you get a jolly good food, nice bed. Do what you like in your room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think the master and mistress were content with their station in life, or do you think they would have liked to hav
e gone a bit higher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh - no, I think they were - at the moment they were - when I was there they was quite all - happy with their life. They had - well they had rise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  up from - from the start. They had got - had a smaller house but then they got to a larger, and I think they were quite contented then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What did you think of them and their way of living? You quite admired these people did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I quite liked the way of - their living. 'Cos I've always been a person what likes to see a nice cl
ean tablecloth and things like that. Nice silver and - everything looking nice, which I'd never had at my young days. In my young -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You found that quite an attractive element did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I found that very attractive. When I was young you see we had
 a scrubbed table, which we had to do three times a week to try and make it white. Which - when you go to places like that, a nice place, you've got nice white cloth on the table. Don't see a scrubbed table, and hearth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 stoned things. It makes all the difference to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You like living with nice furniture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
I like living with nice things. Mm. Not just rubbish. And all your time got to keep scrubbing all the time, and scrubbing the copper and hearth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 stoning that. I like nice things, I always have done, right 'til today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Do you think this would be one reason why you wouldn't have liked factory work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, I wouldn't have liked factory work at all, no. 'Cos I've had to - I would have had to have gone home again you see. And I wouldn't have had much money for meself. Had to give it - quite a lot of it up. Oh no, I wouldn't like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Would you think the sort of reasons you've just given for liking domestic service, do you think these were fairly general with other servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I think t
hey was quite general with other - they were glad enough to get away from their homes. Because majority of them had the same - treatment as I had as a child you see. There was always this - scrubbing and - cleaning up and - your turn to do this and - runn
i
ng errands and getting - your skimmed milk and two pennorth of cracked eggs, there was all that business to do all the time. Well you were glad enough to get out of it, when you were thirteen, and get something different, and it's an eye-opener too. When 
you do get into a nice place. You - you think you've got into Buckin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 ham Palace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You said the first household you went into was rather a dissolute place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 House. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did this affect your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 w of the upper class, because you said that you
r political views were Conservative, did this first household as it were shake your belief in people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
It shook me a bit, yes, it did. It did shake me rather a lot because - I wasn't used to - drink to start with you see. That wasn't allowed in our house. And when I went there to see that - and even the missus - Mrs Williams - they used to go out horse}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 -r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 iding - nearly every day, the horses used to come up the drive, well she used to start off on whisky. Every day. Which killed her.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How old were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She died when she was - thirty-six. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She actually died of drink did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Absolutely. Yes. She never started her day - directly she got downstairs it was a double whisky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And she'd still go out riding every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And s
he went out riding - on that double whisky. Horses used to come to the drive. Of course you don't see horses today, people don't do that kind of thing. But - then you see the horses would come for mistress and master, and they'd go out driving but they wa
s - always - whisky, they wouldn't start off on a nice cup of tea, and a breakfast. Start off on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They sound really hard cases.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Mm. Which -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This must have been quite shattering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Which really did shatter me in the end. Especially 
when - when he came in drunk, that really - that - that really put the - shook me. 'Cos I hadn't seen that in my own home. And I didn't think people like that done that kind of thing. Yes. No, I thought myself, well I didn't think that ever happened, but 
it does. And it shook me. And of course it - I mean it - it's all right if you just see it once but when you - see it quite a let it - wasn't very nice. So I couldn't stand that. Because I'd not been used to that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And they had drinking parties quite regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh drinking parties, yes, always drinking parties. Never had a party without plenty of drink, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And they would have them frequently would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes. Frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say they were a richer household than the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they were a richer household, I must say that, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there much change in your actual standard of living between the two households, regards the food you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, the - the Williams would have - luxu
ry like - game and all things like that you see, but the others would not, just ordinary leg of lamb, pork, or a chicken. But the other people would go in for pheasants and things like that you see, made a lot of difference. They lived very high.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And you used to eat the same food as the people in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, oh yes, yes. They lived very very high indeed. Mm. A lot of difference. If you sleep in a bed with three or four children - and you're going into domestic service, and you're goi
ng to sleep in a bed on your own, which is much nicer isn't it? Even if you have got another servant in the room. See you feel - oh, this is much nicer than home. And you don't want to go back to home any more. See, you'd much rather be in service. Not on
l
y that you see you got everything provided for you. You got a bath, perhaps you never had a bath at home Most of the people those days never had a bath at home. They had a bath in the kitchen, downstairs, in front of the fire, once a week. There you could
 
have a bath every night if you wanted one. No restrictions. If you wanted a bath, you could have one. See you were kept cleaner. Had more food. See if you wanted an apple you could have an apple, if you wanted banana you could have one, you couldn't at ho
m
e. And you couldn't in a factory. Places like that and it was dirtier in the factories. Cleaner in a - in a nice - domestic place. And if you got into a nice one you had - good tips, which was very nice, you could save them up, put them in your bank book.
 Mater of fact that's where I started a bank book. Was at Beckeham. Kent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That was the Thomsons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. I started a bank book there. I started it on me tips. Yes I did. And they used to tip very very well in those days. Yes, oh yes, girls liked go
ing in service. And - if they got a good mistress, she'd give them one or two of their clothes. And if the shoes fit, well you had those as well. You were well looked after. But if you went into a factory you wouldn't have anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You had just moved to the Thomsons and that was in Kent was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How many servants were there there? Was it a larger household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Two. No, not quite so large. Not quite so large, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What were their titles, you were the nanny, was there a cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 A cook and a general servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did they sleep and eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The cook and the general servant slept in one room, and - more or less up in the loft part. And they ate in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Me, I had a little morning room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Is this where you'd supervise the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, where the children are with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have your own bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I had my own bedroom, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This would be near to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How old were the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Four and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You didn't move there until 1918 did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Just talk about the first year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. Four and six they were. Wanted more attention at that age you see. Mm. Boy and a girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there a servants hall or anywhere where the cook and general servant could spend their evenings so to speak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not really, no. Not for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They'd either sit in the kitchen or go upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the mistress supervise all the housework personally or did she just like give out her orders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She gave out her orders, yes. What was to be done during the day and what she wanted and - things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did you get on with the members of this family when you first went there, did you feel at ease with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, I was quite at ease with them, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did the servants and the members of the family address each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Madam - and sir. Yes sir and no sir, yes madam and no madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 That would obviously hold for the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Holds - everyone - like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did the cook and general servant address the children if they saw them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh call them by their names. Christian names, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you feel that they were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Very interested in me, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Did the mistress give what you might call moral guidance to the servants? Did she want to know where you were going on your evening off or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no. No. They never wanted to know where you're going. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They let you look after your own private life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
They let you look after your own private affair, yes. But you always had to be in by ten. There was no - after ten o'clock business with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But if you had free time you could go off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, where you liked, to a friend, yes. Never had to say where you were going or anything like that. Of course she was always pleased if you'd been home to your parents, it's only natural. She liked that. And wanted to know what your parents were - 
they was well and - sisters and brothers. All that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 She'd show an interest in what you'd been doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you feel lonely at all there or did you have enough company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 OH I had quite enough company. Yes, the ch
ildren was quite enough company for me, I didn't want any more company than that. Because once you go out you see, you always meet other nannies with children, and perhaps there's three or four. See then - you'd take 'em to the park or - right through the
 woods and - you was never lonely. Was always something to see or squirrels and different things like that, you'd go and feed them. Which I used to like and so did the children, and always bring something home with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It sounds ideal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was very nice. Yes. 'Cos I - I like the country really. But I wouldn't like to live there - alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this place right in the country?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was in the country, yes. There was a wood right at the top. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Presumably if there were other nannies around there were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Further away. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you ever feel homesick at all while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No, no, I was glad to get away from home. There was so much to do at home you see, do this - it was do this, do the other you see, you had no peace at home, not I was glad to get away. I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You thought you'd gone for something better do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, yes, that I had. I mean I - there wasn't all this manglin to do at home, take - we took in people's mangling, three}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 ha'pence a dozen. And when we - went home there was about three - ch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 air full}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496  right up to the ceiling nearly you had to do. Oh no, I was glad to get away from home. Far too much work at home to do. Had a little more - peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was there anything about this particular place you particularly liked or disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 I liked it because - it was - religious family. Prayers and - I like it, singing hymns. And I could go to a - a little church. I liked that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This was in contrast to the place you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Because I a
lways as a child had to go - to Sunday school, morning, afternoon and evening. And - and I was always brought up and was always singing - hymns. And they would say, come out and - and sing a hymn, stand up there on the platform, and that pleased me immens
ely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So this place was more the sort of atmosphere you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 It was different atmosphere altogether. There wasn't any drinking or - coming home drunk or anything like that, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about the actual domestic routine, was the washing sent out there or did they have someone in to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Half the washing was sent out, like the sheets and pillowcases, the large stuff was sent out. Like the maid's aprons and caps and - which they wore in those days, you never see a cap and apr
on in a shop now do you. They were all sent out to be laundered. And goffered - those days, you know, goffered all up - have - have you ever heard of goffering. That's right, that's right, yes, well the - caps used to be goffered. Used to rather - rather 
smart. Because I wasn't - in the uniform like that, I was just in a - a grey dress, and - had an apron on, but usually the uniform was grey.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who did the other half of the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 The general housemaid. Some - and they had a woman in one - whole day a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Doing any ironing and - rough jobs really. Coal and - things like that, getting up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Who made or mended the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They used to have a woman in for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Another woman still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, what woman u
sed to go round different big houses you see, and - doing the mending. Or take it home with her - to mend and bring it back. Then she used to stop and have tea or if it was in the evening she used to stop and have an evening meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So the household was quite intricate, you had three of you living in, then you'd have one to come in to do the rough work and ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Another one to come in and mend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Well mending because there was rather - a lot of us you see, in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any other what you might call casual people connected with the running of the household in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - Mr - he used to, he used to say what he wanted in the garden and anything like that. What he wanted putting in the garden or if any
thing wanted coming out or the - cutting down and things like that he used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you have a gardener full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 We had a gardener, yes, yes. Yes, rather. That was interesting 'cos we had a large mulberry tree outside the front of the house. V
ery nice when it - with the fruit on. Beautiful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What were your hours and how much free time did you get at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh always the evenings free for myself. When the children were abed, yes. All evening 60 meself. Well then - I was very fond
 of knitting, I used to knit all their - socks and - jumpers and - cardigans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did you get any half days or days off a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Always a Wednesday or a Thursday half day. One whole day a month, and every other Sunday afternoon off, and evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this standard or was this good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Always that - that was quite good though. Yes, it was quite good, yes. It was quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How much time would the children spend with their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 All day Sunday more or less. 'Cos used to be - S
unday school - morning, Sunday school in the afternoon. And of course mummy and daddy used to go. And I'd go along with them, yes. That's if I hadn't - got my - afternoon and evening off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How much time would the children spend with their parents without you there, was there any regular time in the evening or afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Only in the evening, before they went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How long would this be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Might be an hour. Yes, say what they've done during the day you see with their other children -
 and friends. If I let them do different things you see they used to tell their mother and father about it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would the parents ever dress them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no. No, no. No, never dressed them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Or put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no. No. One of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would they take them out shopping or any outings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 If I was with them, yes, shopping. We used to go shopping -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 But not just the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you had more or less full -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Full time of them you see, if they wanted any clothes you see I'd - was there with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Whereabouts would the child see its parents, would they go running in to them in the morning before they got up or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they would like to, many times I couldn't stop 
them so I - just let them go you see, which the father and mother was quite pleased you see, long as they were not there - too long you see. Usually on the Sunday morning that used to be. Not other mornings. And they used to say to me, can I run down to m
ummy and daddy just to get in their bed five minutes, just five minutes. I said, all right then, five minutes only then, then come back. Sunday treat. Yes. And they used to love it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any other like informal occasions like that when they'd see their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes, when they came in or - in - wanted to go and see their mummy and daddy, oh yes Especially if I was out in the garden, we had a swinging chair in the garden, and perhaps having our tea out in the garden you see directly they saw t
heir mummy and daddy you see they'd just rush, mummy and daddy. They'd come forward and - to us you see, sit with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the children have any household tasks to carry out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 None whatever. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the children share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, never shared a bed with anybody, they had their own bed, one each. One each in the same room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 This large house, did it have a separate bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh separate bathroom, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How often did the children bathe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Every night. Every night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Twice a day sometimes. I used to be - liked to take them out rather nice. Of course other nannies you see perhaps - were a little bit better than I was you see in a position, so I used to
 like my children to look as good as their children, it's only natural, so I didn't mind how many times I - changed them. And I used to wash some of their small things out myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So there was quite a lot of like competition between nannies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh 
definitely. The nannies always used to be - nannies used to try and - see who could be the best one of the - three or four of us. Oh yes. And of course the - parents used to hear about this from the other - mothers and fathers of the children, 'cos I mean
 when there was parties you see, all that - lot would get together and we'd have a party, if it was fine it - on the lawn. See. Of course you dressed yours the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So the nannies you met in the park in fact their employers were the same social circle as yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
That's right, and they used to come with their children as well - to the party. Stop. And if I went out you see with the children, I stayed - with the children. See we used to have - singing and games and - one thing and the other. Especia
lly one of the - little girl always used to - stand in the corner and - used to sing. She wouldn't stand in anywhere else, only in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Children are funny like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Where did the children have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 In the morning room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 With you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was this all their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, always had their meals in the morning room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever eat with their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Occasionally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would this be a treat again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, that's a treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Was it a regular Sunday thing or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, more or less a Sunday thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of cooking equipment was there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Gas. Rather a large gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were all the members of the family there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes, they was all there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Being a vicar he didn't have to go off to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. No, no, no, he did - different - times he was in and out all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What sort of food did they have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh porridge and - eggs and bacon and - eggs, scrambled egg, normal English breakfast, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they have anything different on certain days, Sundays or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, just the roast - we used to have and Yorkshire pudding. Or chicken those days. 'Cos we kept - chickens as well. We used to kill}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 one of the chickens and perhaps have a chicken for - Sunday meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they grow their own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Fruit and vegetables, every - everything was grown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were any fruit and vegetables bought at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not many. Not many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they used any tinned or dried fruit and vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. And - not the vegetables. No, no. Fruit. But not the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say you had a gardener, did anyone else do anything to the garden, did the master like gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, he'd go out there and have a go, yes. And so - he said - he said, if you want to - have your little patch with the children, yes, we had a little patch as well. Oh yes. Yes. We was very proud o
f our little patch when we grew things. I let the children - put their flower seeds and lettuce and - all different bits and pieces, they used to love it, so did I. Yes. Oh yes, we had a nice patch of our own. And they used to - pick their things and take
 them in to mummy and daddy and show everybody else and - aunties and uncles what they can do. Oh yes, and they used to want them up in the bedroom too. Little vase of flowers, of their own growing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You say they kept hens, did they keep any other sort of livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were these for the table as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes. Yes. For the table, yes. Plenty of chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did the children and servants have the same food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Everybody had the same food. Was no difference between the servants and - anybody else. All had the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were the children allowed to talk at meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no, no, no. Occasionally they tried it on on Sundays you see but - it didn't work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, they usually had a piece of everything what was on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would happen if they didn't like greens or wouldn't eat something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They still had it on their plate. And we used to make them t
ry, yes, to have it. Because it was good for them, see. I used to, you know, say now come along, I'm going to have a piece now and now you have a piece. It's very good for you. You'll never be a - strong man or a girl unless you have the greens, and carro
ts. Eventually -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You tried to persuade them rather than force them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Yes. Yes, just say things about them you see. And eventually they was quite fond of it all then. But I've never forced food down a child, I don't believe in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What about if they left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well that was - that's quite all right. Yes, that was quite all right, as long as they had - a decent - meal - midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes. Three if they wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about table manners, did you teach them to hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
Oh yes, yes, yes and the way to put it and - oh they knew their manners very very well. They knew what - if there was going to be fish first and meat afterwards, oh yes. And soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could toys or books be taken to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 
No. No, nothing like that, no, never. If there was a book came round, they'd just have to go back and take it upstairs to the nursery. No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You wouldn't allow them in the morning room at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No. Nothing in the morning room, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When could they leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When I told them to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They'd have to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, 'til I'd finished my meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did you feel about the way the parents wanted to bring their children up? Was there any conflict of opinion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh I liked the way they brought the children up very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So you were in agreement?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, I was in agreement with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7548936\charrsid479496 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 s birthdays be different from any other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh - yes, oh rather, we'd have a lovely party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Could you tell us about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh, lot - lots of children and the - cook used to make jellies and a - a cake for the one with candles on. So the - one's
 birthday was put in the middle of the table, the cake, so - they could blow it out, and have all their friends in, doesn't matter whether it was twenty or thirty. Have a real nice party. Then they all had - hats on, afterwards and - different games and t
hey all had presents and balloons to take home with them. All - all very nice it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How about Christmas Day, what would the family do together then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh have a big party. Yes, uncle and aunties and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They'd have people come and stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 People come in, yes. Yes, have a nice do. Very nice indeed. Especially the servants as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 What would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well - give them a nice time and - everything was decorated up. Even the kitchen. All trimmed up everywhere, plenty of trees abo
ut. Plenty of parcels - hanging on them. Espec - we had one in the hall as well. Parcels all round. And after breakfast of course the children had their parcels given to them. And that was in with mummy and daddy and - uncles and aunts. And they used to o
pen them up then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 When would the servants have theirs, open theirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Well they used to do theirs - first thing in the morning. See what they'd got. So did I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Were there any musical instruments in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Piano. And a - a - f
lute. Mother and father played. Yes. The children, the girl - wanted to - Daphne, she was starting - lessons. She was very interested in music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did they ever make music together as a family, did they have musical evenings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, we used to have musical evenings, yes. Yes, a sing-song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you join in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes. Yes. Join in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 You were very much one of the family then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Join in with the singing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 How did this affect your relationship with the other two servants, because you were obviously much more -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh they used to love it, they used to - come in as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 They used to come in as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Yes, when they'd finished everything outside and they used to - Mrs Thomson used to say, now come alo
ng, you can come in now and sit down and - if you can sing, sing. Normal going on, yes. When there's a - party, yes. Then - we'd all join in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 So there wasn't much gulf between the master and the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh no. No, ho, you was - they wasn't - stuck up people like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Did this happen at all at the previous place you were at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 No, no, no, no. No, they were different kind of people altogether. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Would you say they were more snobbish, the first lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Oh yes, well they were drinkers you see. Yes, plenty of drink there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8486024 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 And they wouldn't have the servants joining in anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2387616 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9247805\charrsid479496 Not in - oh no, no, no. Half the time they didn't know what they were doing. So I never - used to let the children go nowhere near an
ything like that you see, kept them - completely away.
\par }}